INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('43', 'It requires a lot of writing. The instructor is harsh on grading. Half of the time the class is fun. Half of the time dull and dreary. Satisfies W and S T-req. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('44', 'Seminar with ALP and a bunch other T req code. Two presentations. Great class if you''re interested in social media and social movements. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('45', 'An easy class. But much more work than I initially expected. Video editing takes a lot of time, so be prepared for that. Prof is very nice, and the class is pretty laid-back. The class has ALP code. The prof sort of expects you to know how to edit films since the beginning and everyone in the class has prior experience with film editing with different softwares. It''s better if you know a little bit of final cut pro before. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('45', 'Editing projects/essay responses after each class. The professor is super niceeee ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('46', 'Class- You don''t learn how to edit in class but she makes you watch Lynda.com tutorials before each class. Weekly projects, usually takes me 6+ hours per week. Prof- nice but boring, likes to show experimental films ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('47', 'I loved the class. We used Final Cut Pro, and a lot of cut practices between scenes. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('48', 'Insanely hard!!!! This is a graduate course. Don''t take it. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('49', 'He is a very interesting professor with a lot to say about films and Brazil. He tries to engage the class well and rewards those that pay attention. Go to office hours. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('50', 'The course is a combination of history and 3d modeling. It has no tests or exams except one vocabulary quiz. The final is graded on a group project, for which students design and build a castle in a chosen location by modeling in Fusion 360. The project also requires a detailed explanation of why you choose the site, where is the quarry, where does your money come from etc. It does not require a lot of time commitment; yet if you are not familiar with medieval history, there are still a reasonable amount of books to read. The class will teach history of castles, a brief history of medieval period, and how to use Fusion 360 with its plugins to build 3-D models. Professor Triplett is really nice and warmhearted. He explains things well and is available at any time. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('51', 'Lots to memorize but easy tests if you do ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('51', 'Easy class if you study for the exams; mostly just go to class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('52', 'intense reading and loads of memorizations and papers. Also a final ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('53', 'Very informative class; no prior knowledge require; Workload is heavy. Don''t take it if you''re not interested in the subject matter. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('54', 'took it as social sci elective, light work load and professor was really good. 1 midterm 1 final and 2 essays. We also visited a museum at chapel hill. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('55', 'I went into this course without any art history experience at all, and Professor Weisenfeld helped me adjust very nicely. She''s always willing to help and adjust office hours to best fit your schedule. She makes you hand write all your notes and takes attendance into account for your grade though. She also doesnt count 93.1 as an A >.> her grading is very reasonable; it''s not hard to get a 100 on an essay. just make sure you try your best and even though art history is subjective, back up your point with proof. kind of contradictory, i know. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('56', 'Prof. Lanzoni is very knowledgeable and passionate about the subject matter. Take it if you are interested in Art History ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('57', 'One of my favorite teachers at Duke; however, this class is graded harshly (most people end up with Bs) ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('58', 'It is a well structured class that does a survey of arts in ''Renaissance France''. The research project of the class is very helpful for anyone interested in art history research. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('59', 'An extremely easy art history course. The professor said ''welcome athletes'' in her course discription. Check if it fulfills any requirements you need. The material is also interesting and good for people with no knowledge in art history or Russia. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('60', 'The class is not hard and the professor is super nice. We have one mid-term one final and one poster project. I think the materials are interesting, and you have to go to every class. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('61', 'This is a great class for those who are interested in the impressionism period. It is very informative on the social history of the movement and focuses on a few prominent artists. Prof Antliff is a great lecturer. ' );
