INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('68', 'Antonio''s class is both about photography and life. Usually, he spent half of the class talking about a specific topic in photography, and the other half sharing his thoughts on life, nature, meditation, water, etc. This class is a good time to relax and learn some photography skill. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('69', 'Painting project biweekly. ~3-5 hours per week outside of class. Professor is helpful. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('69', 'Easy and fun class; but there is a lot of painting homwork ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('70', 'The content is really fun. Have to write weekly report and have in class drawing. The instructor is nice and helpful. Have the opportunity to do sth fun with cool softwares and gadgets ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('71', 'People in class have different levels of background, though Fick is super approachable and acknowledge that. You could do really well even without prior bg in drawing if you are willing to spend extra time. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('71', 'Prof. Fick is very nice. Takes approximately 10 hours per week for big assignments, but you have 2 weeks or up to 1 month to finish it. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('72', 'Pencil/Charcol drawing. Class starts as beginner to intermediate level. One big assignment and 4 sketches every week. Requires more than 8 hours every week and the last assignment takes me >20 hours to finish. Very fun and learned a lot. Recommended if you are ready to commit. Pre-req for sveral visual arts courses. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('73', 'This is a great class where you can really enjoy the creation of arts. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('74', 'The idea of the class is drawing from observations so he doesn''t really teach any technique. It can be a little hard at the beginning since you start to draw from the very first class. But Dr. Fick is very approachable and he is willing to give advice on improving the drawings. You need to draw one finish painting every week on average, and there''s sketch book to finish as well. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('75', '10-20 hours per week, depending on how well if you want to learn. My fav class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('76', 'Great class on PS and a bit of AI. Involved the skills of using these software, though more focus was on principles and elements of design of your digital artwork, which was super helpful ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('77', 'On creating virtual environment and avatars within using OpenSim ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('78', 'In Maya. Focused more on Modeling than Animation (at least when I took it). Learnt a ton of the basics of Maya and 3D Modeling procedures in general ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('79', 'Easy, fun ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('80', 'I loved it. Antonio was amazing and inspiring. Reshaped my view on still images, and the process of art creation. The class meets every week for two and half hours, and there''s simply no workload other than taking couple pictures every week. Requires a DSLR but Mirrorless would also work. Make sure to email him one semester prior in order to get in the class, even if you are going to be on the first window ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('81', 'Nice professor. Almost no readings and homework were all about taking photos. His course is very relaxing and good for anyone with no photography background. Bring an DSLR at least. Also, this is an very popular course, so ask for a permission number as soon as possible. (I asked 1 semesters before enrollment). ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('81', 'Easy photog intro class if you take it with Antonio. His class is more like philosophical, so don''t expect you can learn much techinicals. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('82', 'The class introduces you to logos, posters and other design principles. The prof is pretty organized. The class contains a lot of critique of others'' works. Weekly homework/project that takes about 3-5 hours. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('83', 'Very interesting hands-on class, but the professor is someone who lives in her own world and not someone easy to talk to if you are not really interested in art or this filmmaking topic, and is super strict about cellphones in class. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('84', 'Each student do a semester-long documentary photographic project in Hillsborough, NC. Nice if you like photography and enjoy exploring new places. Not convenient if you do not have a car or cannot drive. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('85', 'Creating motion graphics using Adobe Effect. Design, execute, and critic. Learnt a ton about AE and some basic procedures in creating a piece of film like storyboarding, etc. Did title sequence, trailer, etc. Class is chill though tons of work outside. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('86', 'Senior class for visual arts majors where you develop a project of your own ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('87', 'Coggins is an extremely mediocre professor. He tries to make things ~relevant to medicine since the class is 90% pre-meds but mostly he just comes off as over-earnest and obnoxious. That said, class format has changed slightly: there are now weekly quizzes on Sakai and the tests are multiple multiple choice. The quizzes are often poorly worded and very specific so consult with others when you do them. There is no more paper though, woohoo! ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('88', 'Requires fair amount of study. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('89', 'Good lecturer, not hard to grasp the idea of it but requires a lot of memorization. The free response questions are kind of hard in the sense of answering everything he wants ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('90', 'Great course for science and engineering students! Talked about skills for communicating science to the general public/press/other scientists. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('91', 'Very easy class for college requirements ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('92', 'Professor is really helpful and clear. There is a quiz every two weeks. The material is not hard. You will get an A if you work hard ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('93', 'great gateway course for bio majors; lab involves gene cloning and cool bio-techs and I personally love this course ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('93', 'Material isn''t bad, but presented in an uninteresting way. McClay tells good stories but he also tends to speed through lectures. Haase is smart and sarcastic/witty, sometimes overly so (asked a girl if she was thinking when she asked a question). Multiple-multiple choice is annoying, but if you''re good at understanding the big picture and unconcerned with the details, you''ll be fine. Also, don''t read the textbook, just look for the answers for the reading quizzes. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('94', 'If you have to take the class, take it in spring. Spring class has a more reasonable structure and lectures will be more organized ' );
