INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('209', 'Easiness: The class is pretty easy. There are lots of opportunities for extra credit. The hardest thing about this class is deciphering her instructions for assignments.Workload: The amount of homework is consistent each week: 1 assignment, 1 APT set (small coding exercises), and 1 lab (which is usually finished during lab section). Assignments, APTs, and labs do get harder as the semester progresses, and I probably spent around 5-6 hours on the aforementioned homework near the end of the course.Comments: Professor Rodger is not the best lecturer, but her class is very organized and the course website she has is a godsend. The textbook she uses is also very good for learning Python and some computer basics. Overall, this class was pretty fun, and I would recommend doing all the extra credit assignments because they provide you a really nice grade buffer in the end. However, this course does not do a good job of preparing you for COMPSCI 201. ' );
