INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('244', 'Everything you can learn in this class can be self-taught from the textbook. The professor is very nice, but a bit difficult to understand at first because of his accent. You are allowed a single page of notes to use as a cheat sheet on both midterms and final exams (you can type it or write as small as you want). The material itself is not too difficult. He posts most of his notes online so look at those for sample problems. Also do the problem sets; they aren''t very difficult and he uses varations of those problems on exams (or problems from class). Overall a pretty easy class. Not the most fun or entertaining, but required for all CS majors. ' );
