INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('322', 'Workload is pretty light while material is conceptually hard. Prepare to read the latest papers from the Internet giants. A lot of fun if you''re a system person. Grading is generally lenient. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('323', 'Great intro on distributed system, which is super useful in real-world. Prior knowledge in computer network helped a lot. More knowledge-based though there are two medium-size assignments in C and a research-involved final project of your choice ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('324', 'Great intro on the data intensive systems out there in pratice. Their principles and tradeoffs. Both the high-level picture and very detail-oriented on the core general concepts. Work in group on one of those system as a semester-long project ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('325', 'Hardcore class. A lot of slides per lecture and hard to take in. HWs take a lot of time but are graded rather leniently. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('326', 'Great class on image recognization and image reconstruction (these two topics rotate, when I toke it it was recognization). Very knowledge based (math/stats involved) though also had tons of chances to build your own image classifiers through assignments. Tomasi is so clear in everything. One of the harder classes I had but absolutely loved it. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('327', 'Great professor. He cares about you and you can ask homework questions during office hours. Tests are ok but you need to study for them. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('328', 'It''s a typical graduate class. The workload is not heavy at all. We have in total 6 homework. Each one contains about 5 problems. This class is the next level class after CS330. So the lecture will cover a variety of topics including basic network flow, randomized algorithm and approximation algorithm. Prof. Munagala is a nice guy. His lecture speed is just right and have very intuitive lecture style so I do recommend this class to all students interested in algorithm area. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('329', 'Go through every step in creating a compiler (from a language called Tiger to MIPS). Build one of your own. Great class that is challenging, fun and would help you understand way more of how computer and your programs function ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('330', 'materials are very abstract and very cutting-edge. it feels more like a high level math class than a typical CS class. Ron Parr is a great professor and the expectations are pretty clear. exams are challenging but Ron Parr is reletivey linient with grading. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('331', 'Hard class with good materials and chill grading. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('331', 'Don''t take this class if you hate proofs and don''t expect it to be easy. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('332', 'Workload not big; only two hw assignments, but final project can take a long time; The topics are pretty interesting. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('333', 'Workload is light. Only one final project and one homework. Prof. Panigrahi is a really great lecturer. He lecture his material super clearly. This class will cover topics like network flow, traveling salesman, Hamiltonian Path, etc. You will learn algorithms used to tackle these famous problems. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('334', 'He’s pretty chill and funny. 4-5 homework, averagely take up 6-8hours. One take home midterm and one take home final. He’s lecture is sometimes a bit boring ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('335', 'Workload is not too heavy, only 4 homework and a take home final. Prof. Ge is very very nice. He''s a true gentleman with soft voice and charming appearance. His lecture makes sure everyone in the class understand the material. And he does understand different mathematical background students may have so don''t worry about this. I do recommend this class to students interested in algorithms and their applications. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('336', 'The overload is light. You only get 1 homework and 1 final project. Prof. Panigrahi is a great professor who lectures these difficult materials with crystal clear logic and elegant structure. The class will cover a variety of topic on algorithms and you can set your feet on this land of NP-Complete problem. Throughout the course, you will learn various clever techniques to tackle these notoriously hard problem. I do recommend this class and the professor to everyone interested in algorithm area. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('337', 'The homework every week is basically developing new android mobile apps following the instruction and then update your personal blog. The professor is super easy-going. It was a fun and easy class - recommended! ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('339', 'High recommend if you are interested in anthropology or healthcare; 100-200 pages of reading every week, 1-page single-space weekly response, 2 papers, 2 exams, 1 group project; materials include a mixture of fun ethnographies and dense theories ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('340', 'Fun class. Cross listed with polsci and ics. Contain many good topics regarding humanities. Grading fine. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('341', 'Tried to fulfill my CCI and CZ requirements. Interesting Stuff. A lot of readings and three quizzes with one unannounced. Need to put in effort and do the readings. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('341', 'Really great teacher and really interesting class. A lot of reading though. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('342', 'Easiness: The class is easy if you attend all the lectures. Your grade is based off of two pop quizzes, three midterms (which are multiple-choice/short answer and two essays), and a final paper. How well you do on your midterms depends on how much of his lectures you can regurgitate and the TA grading your essay. Not a hard class; my class’s average final grade ended up being an A-, which is typical of the course.Workload: There is reading assigned each week. These readings can be helpful on the essay section of your midterm. Pop quizzes are normally three easy questions based off of the readings, and Professor Starn makes huge hints about when quizzes are, so most of the class just did the readings whenever he made hints. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('342', 'Knowledgable professor, interesting lectures, make sure to take notes because they will be on the tests. Good amount of readings, but you don''t have to read them all to do well on the tests. Class average A-. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('343', 'Wonderful class, super chill, have to compose a piece of music, but other than that, basically no work. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('344', 'Makes you think about things you take for granted for society. Changed my perspective on everyday life. ' );
