INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('395', 'Probably the easiest ECE core class conceptually besides ECE 110. The lab is very chill, there are only 7 labs and you work in groups of 3 so you do not need to spend longer than 2 hours per week on lab reports. Homework can be a bit long but there are a lot of office hours every week. Lastly, Dr G is a legend: he explains the concepts very well during class so make sure you go to class as his notes might not be very complete. Furthermore, Dr G also gives a few homework assignments with MATLAB and Maple components to help students gain a more fundamental understanding of the concepts being taught in class. The exams, meanwhile, are similar to those given by Dr G in ECE110 or EGR103, whereby the structure of each exam is consistent. I highly recommend taking this course if Dr G is teaching it. ' );
