INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('485', 'Great for getting into finance careers, mainly markets and S&T content, grade mainly consists of case competitions/stock pitch competitions that you have to hand it, workload is light, professor is cool ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('486', 'Light workload, finance must ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('487', 'Very basic and broad knowledge for investment banking. Is OK as a preparation for IBD career. There are pop quizs and a final written exam. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('487', 'Open to all sophomores; half-credit, graded, a few pop quiz + 1 final exam; take this class if you are thinking about doing an investment banking internship; this is basically Recruiting 101 ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('487', 'Very manageable half-credit class that helps you establish a basic understanding of the finance industry. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('488', 'Course offered only in the spring semester, specifically for sophomores who are interested in upcoming finance recruiting. Strongly recommend if applied to you. As the name suggests, very practical stuff is taught, and Emma and John are the best resource at Duke for finance. Grading is based on several finance competitions you participated. There''s no clear curve policy, but it''s lenient. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('488', 'Easy class; three competitions in finance to decide your grade; if you get decent scores on each one you get an A; as long as you submit everything, you should be in the A range. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('489', 'Recruiting 101 for finance-interested sophomores, enough said... ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('489', 'Easy A, grade is based on projects throughout the semester and one midterm exam. Easy class, must-take for sophomores who want to learn things for their summer finance internship ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('489', 'Highly recommend for people want to find finance internships. Workload itself is not heavy, the competitions could be time consuming; but if you plan to do those competitions anyway, this class would be very helpful. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('489', 'Highly recommend if you’re interested in finance because it teaches you interview contents ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('489', 'easy class with few competitions throughout the semester ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('490', 'Workload light, useful for interviews. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('491', 'Great class. Fun and easy ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('491', 'The other accounting class at Duke. Based halfly on the Econ 174 class, but you can still get a good grade if you did not ace in the previous course. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('491', 'Wasn’t as useful as 174 and it doesn’t count toward Econ major. Don''t take it unless you''d love to have a career in accounting or really interested ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('492', 'Continues the materials from ECON 174. The workload is quite light. No homework submission. Useful if you want to learn something about company''s internal accounting ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('492', 'This class is a continuation of 274. Pre-req is 174. Format and level of difficulty is similar to 174. Good class to take during senior year. Could be useful for a finance track. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('493', 'Interesting class, discussion oriented, make sure you participate in class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('494', 'One presentation and one final paper. Pretty chill class. A lot of readings. The professor is very nice. Participation required. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('495', 'Duke in NY program. Great professor. Grading based on 2 essays and 2 midterms. Will need to memorize a lot of facts/dates. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('496', 'Workload is very manageable and I highly recommend the professor. John is one of the best lecturers and mentors you can get at Duke. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('496', 'John is a great lecturer and the materials are very interesting. Highly recommend if you are considering a career in finance. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('496', 'John is really smart and chill and he makes sure you understand the material without giving any unnecessary work. His lectures are very clear and I think this topic is worth learning if you are interested in going into finance. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('496', 'The workload is not heavy. The materials are not difficult. The professor is very nice. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('497', 'Two midterms and two papers, each 25% of the final grade; midterms are straightforward T/F and short answer questions if you take detailed notes in class. Grading on papers is somewhat arbitrary depending on your TA. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('497', 'The class is listed in cultural anthropology and it is not strongly related to economics. Exams go very into detail, which means you better write down every point Piot says in class. Not an easy A class but you should be able to get an A or A- if you memorize the notes and understand the reasoning. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('498', 'Light workload ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('499', 'Low workload, prof is quite clear and overall a good lecturer ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('500', 'chill class, lecture-based. two papers. fulfills CZ. do it if u like writing. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('500', 'Two papers, weekly blogs. Not too bad but be ready to listen to lots of info - class material is important. It’s a cz too so some historical stuff too ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('501', 'Readings could be difficult, heavy emphasis on reading responses/essays in grading but can''t get feedback during the semester about which grade you fall into ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('501', 'Workload is okay. A lot of reading and one reading response per week. But if just skimming through readings that''s manageable. Quite interesting class. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('502', 'Challenging materials and philosophical reasoning, an interesting and different perspective to examine economics; prior econ classes are helpful ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('502', 'Readings are dense but not unmanageable. If you don''t have economics experience don''t take it. If you''re looking for an easy econ elective don''t take it. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('503', 'Very light course load. Broad economic overview of the economic sector, very interesting. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('504', 'I took this class because it was both an Economics elective and ALP, so in reality I wasn''t that interested in the material the class covered. The course could have been interesting, but Prof De Marchi, though a very very nice man, is definitely not a good teacher...He rambles and loses track of where he is. All coursework is completed in groups, and the final ''research paper'' weighs heavily (was at a B+/A-, then he gave my group an A+...). Arbitrary grading, basically. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('505', 'Can learn a lot. Group research project counts 75%. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('505', 'Lecture based. Prof is Italian and is really difficult to understand. Content can be interesting if you like art. One semester-long research paper in groups. Have to work hard to get a good grade ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('505', 'Lectures are boring, but you can learn a lot if you are interested in art history. Much application of economics/market knowledge. Has a R code and has weekly assignment (progress report) on a semester-long research paper, group work based. Grades are not great ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('506', 'A very research oriented class. Background in statistics or econometrics is very helpful. A lot of extra readings but not too many are actually required. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('507', 'Great professors, very indepth discussions. Reading about 20+ pages articles per session. Participation highly valued. Challenging but worthwile class. Good mix of economics/business and philosophy/theorizing. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('508', 'Very nice professor. 3 exams + frequent responses + final research project. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('508', 'Not much workload. Nice professor. The research paper is a group project. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('509', 'Easy class with low workload, but a bit unclear about exam grading, maybe not an easy A class. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('510', 'Light workload, easy class overall ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('511', 'Workload is light, materials are kind of boring but easy. An essay class with easy exams and easy assignments. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('511', 'Material is a bit dry but not hard. She is sometimes unstructured ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('512', 'Miller is super sweet and easy with grading paper. 3 exams during the semester, which you can do well as long as you memorize stuffs on her PPT before the exams. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('513', 'Two paper assignments decide your grade. No exams. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('514', 'Two papers for the whole semester, no other work ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('514', '2 papers (10-15 pages single-spaced), papers are on interesting topics that you can choose ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('514', 'Just two really long papers plus participation; Grace is nice but pretty strict ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('514', 'Two papers for the whole semester that''s it. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('515', 'It has one midterm, one project, one final, and quizes. Not very hard, but the class is poorly organized. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('515', 'Prof is very very funny and chill. She teaches about how the different financial institutions work, and invites guest speakers to talk about markets and current events. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('516', 'An easy finance electives taught by a Wall Street Veteran. Mary''s a math PHD and her other fixed income class is good as well ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('517', 'Go to every class, do the problem sets and you will be fine. Exams are basically the same as problem sets. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('518', 'Duke in NY Study Away--ask me personally if you have questions. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('519', 'Pretty long problem sets + debate + policy paper and presentation. Prof changes up the structure of the course each year. Topics are interesting but are not really related to poverty, so take another course if you want to learn about developmental econ. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('520', 'One of my favorite clsses ever. An amazing professor. You have a lot of outside lecturers from different areas of finance and different companies. You also get a good glimpse into some basic finance-related concepts. Rasiel is a very fair and straightforward professor. The workload is minimum. No final or midterm. There were problem sets on the syllabus but we never did any of them. There are 5 essays and participation is VERY CRUCIAL. You must ''apply'' to get into the class (ie. send Rasiel your resume and cover letter/letter of interest). She takes mostly all juniors with the exception of 1-3 sophomores. Highly recommended. Great for networking as well. Rasiel is an amazing resource if you''re at all interested in finance. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('521', 'Super chill and relaxed class featuring multiple senior level guest speakers from Wall St. Emma usually teaches the course but John''s is much easier so I''ve heard. Discuss current events and very basic finance topics such as options, bubbles, interest rates etc. It is a writing course and grade was based on 3 papers. Need to send resume to Emma & John and be selected for the course since it is a 18 person class. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('522', 'Duke in NY program. There would be a market update every lecture. Grading based on 2 quizzes and 3 essays. Very engaging lectures. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('523', 'The workload is not heavy. The materials are not difficult. The professor is very nice. You need to follow the financial markets for this course. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('523', 'Class covers basic functions in investment bank and how market works. Highly recommend for those who want to work in finance, especially market. Workload is very manageable and John prepares you very well for a career in S&T. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('523', 'Minimal work and material very relevant to recruiting interviews, especially for markets roles ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('523', 'This class is super helpful if you are interested in sales and trading because it covers the basics of bonds, foreign exchange, etc and John is very knowledgeable about these topics. We also talked a lot about the market and news. I liked the paper topics and you learn a lot from writing the papers. If you have taken econ 372 this class can be a little repetitive. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('524', 'Very informative and fun. John is the most interesting prof I have ever had. I took it in London so the workload is light. Highly recommend taking the course at Duke ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('525', 'not much work to do, 3 essays + 1 quiz + participation grade. be prepared to talk a lot during class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('526', 'LOVE John so much. Funny, fast thinking, old-school Wall Street trader who can keep talking for years. Talk about markets every day in class, and really interactive sessions, with him and guest speakers. Good way to learn about different roles in Finance and network with people. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('527', 'Medium difficulty, low workload. They have textbook but it is not required and the slides cover everything in homework and exams. The medium is B+. Professor is nice and chill but regrading is nearly impossible. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('527', 'Not very heavy workload; not very hard ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('527', 'Easy A+ ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('528', 'She''s a cool professor and knows a lot about finance. Really helpful for people interested in finance. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('529', 'Rasiel may not be the best lecturer in the world (unfortunately I often didn''t go to class), but she is very passionate about Finance and knows a lot of side-facts that go along with the basic lecture material. She teaches off powerpoints, so it''s easy to just study off them for the final. In the Fall, it is mandatory to participate in a case competition, so if you don''t want to do that, take the class in the spring, Overall, not a tough class at all. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('529', 'You have to do the finance competition if you are in the class in the fall semester. Those competitions are extremely helpful if you want to have a career in the financial service industry ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('529', 'Very useful for finance intervies. You have to participate in 2 out of 3 competitions as part of the class grades. You really learn a lot from the class and competition. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('530', 'Core finance class for the concentration. A lot of people spend their time sucking up to Rasiel for potential internships. The class itself is not terribly difficult. Very basic finance-related information. Your grade is based on 1 FEP competition, 8-ish problem sets, and a final exam. In the spring, you will have a midterm instead of the competition. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('531', 'Definitely one of the classes that you have to take at Duke. Rasiel is an expert, from whom you will learn a lot about finance in general. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('531', 'Super useful class. Learned a lot but must work hard to get good grades. Material is not the hard part; the assignments and projects are. Still recommended. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('531', 'Regular workload, professor is very good in instructing the course. Easy if you go to class/read the notes. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('531', 'The materials are useful if you are interested in finance. Competitions are great learning experience, but you can avoid them in one of the semesters. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('532', 'Manageable workload. Learned a LOT about finance industry and interview questions that will be asked during recruitment. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('532', 'Fun professor. Not too much work. If you''re interested in a career in finance, then consider taking it sophomore year. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('532', 'Very knowledgeable professor. Nice in person. Definitely take this class if you''re interested in finance. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('532', 'In general an easy class. Emma is a great professor. Learned a lot about basic finance and asset class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('533', 'Clear explanation, lecture suffice to understand the materials, 1 problem set every 1-2 weeks ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('534', 'Not too hard, I liked Rasiel. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('534', 'I took it in the spring and we had one midterm + 3 case studies. If you take it in the fall you''ll most likely do two finance competitions instead. I''ve heard a lot of mixed things about whether you should take it in the spring/fall - in my opinion, the class material wasn''t hard at all and the curve was okay in the spring. If you are seriously considering a career in finance, I would suggest you take it as early as possible. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('535', 'Intro level finance clas, easy and quite useful ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('535', 'Not very hard, as long as you understand all the lecture notes ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('535', 'Not much workload, 3-4 hours a week; tests are easy but the grade is not curved;attendance not mandatory ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('536', 'Great professor but I am not into finance so the material is dry ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('536', 'Requirement for Econ major / finance minor. Useful and easy. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('536', 'She tends to be conceptual, workload was ok. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('537', 'Workload is light with 1 ps per week. Good foundation class for anyone interested in finance. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('537', 'Emma is very good at teaching and has boat loads of experiences at finance. The midterms are fair and so are the problem sets. However, she does not write a lot of notes on the board. However, I would recommend taking this course with her ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('537', 'Good course, if our time in you will learn a lot ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('537', 'cool class, useful lectures if you are into real world finance, acceptable workload ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('538', 'Manageable workload. Easy but useful materials. Great professor. So go to classes as she always talks things that are not written on powerpoint. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('538', 'she reuses the tests ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('539', 'Loved Fullenkamp. If you are interested in finance, or investment banking specifically, take Corp Fin with him. He is super smart and funny. It is a lot of work (biweekly problem set/short essay), but it''s super useful if you are going into investment banking. Plus he''s actually pretty lenient on grades. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('539', 'Very very useful and fun class. A lot of corporate finance material to cover and the essay topics are very fun. He''s got a humor but also loves to make fun of people. Grading is not harsh. This class and financial accoutning are the only two classes that will really benefit your investment banking interviews. (IBD) ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('539', 'The workload is crazy, but Fullenkamp is a really funny guy and the materials are extremely interesting. Highly recommend when you have the time for the work. Paper and Problem set every other week. Quizes every other week and a final and term paper. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('539', 'great professor / best class at Duke if you are interested in an IBD career ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('540', 'Best class I have ever take at Duke. Be mindful of the workload ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('541', 'Interesting professor, heavy workload, wall street students, wall street vibe ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('542', 'Very difficult class, because there is a lot of material to cover, and there is a ton of work (either a problem set or a 3 page short essay due every week - set on Friday and must be completed by the coming Monday + quizzes after every pset is due + final paper + final exam). However, Prof Fullenkamp, though slightly intimidating and very comfortable with calling people out, is a very clear professor, and his lectures are easy to follow. Overall, you learn a lot. My advice: DO NOT SKIP A SINGLE LECTURE, OR YOU WILL FALL BEHIND. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('543', 'interesting class, high workload, demanding writing assignments ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('544', 'Only two assignments throughout the whole semester without any other exam. Grade is based on those two assignments and class participation. Professor is nice but she merely reads from her notes. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('544', 'Light workload ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('545', 'chill. 2 papers. class is pretty much useless. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('546', 'Duke in New York class, light workload, easy materials, easy grading, professor is very nice. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('547', 'Duke in NY Study Away--ask me personally if you have questions. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('548', 'Workload is not too bad, but lecture could be very dry. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('549', 'Professor Tauchen is very nice but lectures can be boring at times. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('550', 'great class. Taught by DUMAC people ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('550', 'Great class if you are interested in asset management and relevent finance knowledge in general. A broad cover of different aspects in finance and similar to many stuff covered in CFA level 1 ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('551', 'Took it for the ECON code but the content is barely relevant to economics. Professor brings in different speakers; biweekly reading responses and one semester-long research project either in group or individual. Mainly interacted with my TA during TA discussion sessions (biweekly), seldom go to lectures although the professor is kinda famous ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('552', 'Really cool and easy econ/history/AAAS elective. The whole course ONLY consists of participation and one research paper. Talks about various labor systems such as slavery, indentured servitude, coolies and other topics such as black social mobility, racial ideology and the great migration. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('553', 'Duke in NY Study Away--ask me personally if you have questions. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('554', 'This is the first time it has been offered and not sure if it will be offered again but definitely apply if it is and if you’re interested in finance ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('555', 'Previous econometriics knowledge would be very helpful. Very irrevelant to investment banking or S&T. Essentially a stats class with some application in finance field. The professor is from U.K and his British accent is ''mesmerizing'' I fell into sleep pretty often. But he''s a great professor if you can pay attention. The test is not hard actually. But you will be disappointed if you think this class can better prepare you for the finance field. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('556', 'Counted as one finance concentration elective; interesting to take it if you haven''t taken ECON 210, there are plenty of overlap between them; workload less than ECON 372 ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('557', 'Not a hard class but the professor''s very bad at explaining things. You just need to learn everything by yourself. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('557', 'The class was kinda disorganized. You have to do the readings in order to do well in the class. The content is not hard. Attendence is very necessary ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('558', 'Professor likes to go off on tangents - otherwise an interesting course about how economics can be used to determine the efficiency of certain laws, especialy ones to do with contracts and liability. His office hours are very helpful for the homeworks, he''ll basically tell you the answer ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('559', 'Easy A for a 400-level Econ class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('559', 'Boring class yet useful class. The material are actually interesting. Could be an option for Econ electives.Only midterms. No papers. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('559', 'you need to study hard for it ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('560', 'Only written notes in class so participation is recommended. Very interesting topics about competitions between companies, and the professor is super nice. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('561', 'Very interesting material about oligopoly and very applicable to real life situations. Professor doesn''t take attendance but all notes are written on the white board so you need to go to class. Very reasonable workload - 8 problem sets 1 midterm 1 final ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('561', 'Very interesting topic delivered by knowledgable and clear professor. Porblem sets sometimes get difficult but manageable if you go to office hours. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('561', 'Excellent professor, very insightful class and actually more applicable than I expected. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('562', 'Professor is very kind and knowledgeable although lecture can be a bit dull at times. Very small workload, no weekly assignment, lectures are recorded, and practice exams are helpful for studying for midterms and finals. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('563', 'A lot of overlap with Econ 372. Took it in london. The workload was nothing. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('564', 'Maths oriented finance class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('565', 'It is also a grad-level class, a theoretical version of Econ 372. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('566', 'Didn''t really go to class, unfortunately - Prof. Bollerslev let''s you choose whether you want to complete homeworks (2 over the semester) and midterm, so technically you could just do the final and get away with it. A lot of his questions are based on what he says in class, so might be a good idea to go (which I didn''t....smh). Not a hard class overall. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('567', 'Clear and engaging instructor. Workload is okay. Attendance not required. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('568', 'YES THIS IS AN EASY A class but takes lot of efforts. You have to take this class or independent study for honor thesis. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('569', 'EXCELLENT PROFESSOR. Every econ major should have her. Chill class. Easy grade SO FAR. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('570', 'Good if you''re doing cookie cutter empirical thesis, useless and frustrating otherwise. You write a massive research proposal that''s half the length of the actual thesis, but really doesn''t prepare for anything besides the introduction part. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('571', 'Don''t take it with Kimbrough. Too much workload and unhelpful professor in general. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('572', 'Great professor for thesis!!! If you have him as one of your choices, don''t hesitate since he gives really good and constructive comments for your thesis ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('573', 'An experienced and knowledgeable professor from China; Discussion-based seminar; Readings are thought provoking ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('573', 'For those of you who think you lack a deeper understanding of domestic politics, economics and international relationships, this is an easy class to start with, no workload, you can learn a lot ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('573', 'This class allows you to learn China''s political economy and geopolitics in the Asia-Pacific region in a very free style way. Very easy class and you will learn a lot of interesting stories and sociology theories ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('574', 'Hard math class. Don''t take it with this professor! ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('575', 'Very homework assignment based; explained a lot from ECON 372 about how the graphs are drawn, but there is very limited ECON stuff in it, pretty math-intense ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('576', 'Curve is very generous, though materials are advaced. Grad-lvl class. Easy A ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('577', 'No a hard class for a math major, but has a lot more math stuff going on compared with a normal econ class. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('578', 'Only one final in Nov, no midterms, 70% grade in HW, group-based. Funny guy from France, very nice, and lovely way of teaching. Interesting materials to learn, and useful if want to work in ST.. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('579', 'Not too hard, homework done in teams, very light workload, open-book final, professor thinks he''s humorous ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('580', 'This is a very group-project based class. Choose your group wisely. Material is not mathematically hard but can be calculation heavy. A good course to take if you plan on taking two math courses during the semester and want to to balance the overall course load. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('581', 'Easy intro course which gives you some understanding of the K-12 education system in US. Linght workload but have to compelete 18 hours'' tutroing at local schools. Professor Anderson is awsome and really cares about her students but can be slow in giving hoework feedbacks. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('581', 'Service learning class with some reading and reflection assignments ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('582', 'Service in local school required. A lot of discussion and group work. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('583', 'Service-learning class; small workload; nice professor ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('584', 'This class is relatively easy in terms of class materials.You will be required to write a lot of short papers and reflections of tutoring (you will be required to go to a local school twice a week to tutor a kid or several kids)but papers are easy to write! Unlike other Educ 101, this class taught by Shane has 2 exams but you will be able to drop the lower score one. I would say getting an A is very managable if you work hard! BTW, Professor Shane usually dominated the class by his speeches but most of the times, his speeches were fun! ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('585', 'Incredibly easy, slightly boring, and a service learning class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('586', 'Super easy. You can get an A as long as you finish the work. This class has a lot of codes for the general education requiremnt ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('587', 'FOCUS class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('588', 'Very interesting to actually go an photograph a school. Not hard to do well but professor expects you to put in a little effort but definitely gives you lots of support to do so. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('589', 'Katie is really nice and care about her students. The class itself is not hard and there aren''t many writing work to do. There''s free writing in class but it seems like the grading is based on your attitudes. It''s a service learning class so get ready for 2 teaching session every week! It is interesting though ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('590', 'Most life changing class I''ve taken. Deep exploration of what it means to be asian in higher education. I really liked everyone in my class and even though I didn''t really try for the final paper, I still did well in the class. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('591', 'If you are in Pratt, this is the very first course you take as a Pratt student. It''s a required course and it teaches you how to use Matlab, which is a computational software that will come in handy in many of the later engineering courses. It''s offered in both fall and spring semesters but most people take it in the fall. It can be a little bit overwhelming at the start if you are new to programming but there''s tons of help available from professors and TAs. Dr. G (Gustafson) is an excellent teacher. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('592', 'Easy A class. Labs are extemely useful. Do lab homework and you''ll be fine. Lecture optional. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('592', 'intro class for engineering. Learn MATLAB and Latex. Dr. G is an interesting professor. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('592', 'Quite a bit of work each week including weekly labs and such. Overall the course material I thought was interesting and relatively easy. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('592', 'Dr. G and Simmions are great ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('593', 'You basically have to take it anyways if you are in Pratt, Dr. G is pretty cool ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('593', 'weekly assignment is in the form of lab, consisted of several questions; not very difficult; professor is very clear and interesting ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('594', 'Learn to use matlab and latex. There is a 3-hour lab every week, and a latex-edited lab report (not difficult, but can be very time consuming). Dr.G is very good at explaining things. ' );
