INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('744', 'Fascinating class, professor is an incredible speaker. Not a lot of work either. Would recommend ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('745', 'Don''t take this class! It''s so much work and horrible grades!! He gives you books and long readings to read for every class, 6 pop reading quiz all about details from the book, 2 papers, three blog posts, and a final. This class is cross-listed with many different departments, and you will see lots of people BS so much with no insights at all. And he''s the toughest grader I''ve ever seen at Duke. Even if you work super hard and go to the office hours, you will still end up with terrible grades or even withdraw for many. His grading is very arbitrary, and you won''t know what he wants out of your essays. If you don''t want this unpredictable challenge or even damage on your transcript, don''t take his class. If you really want to learn about the topic, take other classes in environmental sciences or stuff, NOT this one! ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('745', 'Don''t take this class! It''s so much work and horrible grades!! He gives you books and long readings to read for every class, 6 pop reading quiz all about details from the book, 2 papers, three blog posts, and a final. This class is cross-listed with many different departments, and you will see lots of people BS so much with no insights at all. And he''s the toughest grader I''ve ever seen at Duke. Even if you work super hard and go to the office hours, you will still end up with terrible grades or even withdraw for many. His grading is very arbitrary, and you won''t know what he wants out of your essays. If you don''t want this unpredictable challenge or even damage on your transcript, don''t take his class. If you really want to learn about the topic, take other classes in environmental sciences or stuff, NOT this one! ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('746', 'Hard class. Tons of reading. Tests are brutal and make you question your intelligence. Group projects are a pain. Stewart is a great and fascinating person though. If you don''t mind struggling, you will learn a LOT, especially with regards to current/recent epidemics (Ebola, Zika). ' );
