INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('754', 'Heavy work load. Grade is determines by multiple tests and tasks. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('755', 'Weekly responses, 3 short papers. Tends to be quite philosophical (deconstructing Eurocentric narratives) but can be repetitive at times. Overall a good intro with low workload. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('756', 'It is an interesting class if you are interested in the material. It has a moderate to large amount of reading per week. However, since the class only meets once a week, you would have enough time to finish the reading. Class attendance is important but participation is not necessarily required. No midterm or final. Midterm is composed of several short essays. You can do well on the essays if you have done the reading and tried. Prof. Miller is very reasonable and a fair grader. The class is pretty interesting given its subject matter. It is not only history, but also pretty on philosophy If there''s what you are interested, you would enjoy this class. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('757', 'Take with a different prof. This prof is dry and not super engaging, although she guides you through historical research methods quite well. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('758', 'This course counts as a history elective for PubPol majors. Interesting class and amazing prof. Go to lectures and take notes. Readings are pretty much optional. Two short papers (by short I mean 3 pages) + 1 midterm and 1 final (Formate: IDs and essays). Try to get Eladio as your TA. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('759', 'the class is a huge lecture, and the majority are white looking for an easy a. yet, the grading depends very much on the ta, so go to the office hours. the class is pretty superficial, introducing you to some concepts without going deep into analysis. i personally don''t like this class, it''s kind of depressing and marginalizing. i wouldn''t recommend this class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('760', 'Professor Wilson is the man and he is the dean of the history department. Great choice for Pubpol history elective ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('761', 'Easiness: This is a very easy class with one midterm, one or two papers, and a final. Honestly, not very difficult at all, and in my opinion, easier than the AP US History course I took as a junior in high school. Make sure to read up on ratemyprofessors.com, and take this course even if there is a lot of reading because you don’t have to do them all or even any. Lecture, however, is important. Workload: Extremely light. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('762', 'Lectures were interesting at first but started getting boring; readings are optional; Dean Wilson is just a great human being; tests are easy, but taking notes during class is important ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('763', 'Light workload. Very in-depth materials. Grading depends largely on the TA. Very funny professor who likes to make jokes with students. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('764', 'Took it for pub pol history elective req, at first I didn''t like the course, the class is white-dominated and it was like brain-washing. But it got better and you have a good grasp of contemporary American history. Try to get notes from people who''ve taken the course, that will make your life easier. Midterm was straightforward. You will do fine if you get a nice TA ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('765', 'This was hands down one of my favorite classes at Duke, if not the favorite. The professor is so passionate, eloquent, and competent that class is genuinely enjoyable. Plus, the class size is small (and I anticipate it will probably remain on the smaller side) allowing for the formation of in-class friendships! Yayyy ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('766', '100+ pages of reading per week and three to four presentations per semester. Professor is very nice and insightful. Harsh grader. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('767', 'FOCUS cluster “Humanitarian Challenges”; Smart professor, lots of readings (sometimes very boring), class discussions are graded, 5 short writings and 1 paper are expected. Overall, not a hard class. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('768', 'Easy class. Not a lot of assignment and the professor is nice in grading. But can be a bit dry. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('769', 'Professors are responsible and really care about students; Lectures are informative but not boring at all; Strong recommended for everyone who is interested in Chinese history ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('770', 'Interesting class, approachable professor, not hard to get a good grade ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('771', 'Not hard. Medium reading. Class participation is very important. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('772', 'I would highly recommend Professor Sosin. Even though the reading could be rough, he actually made the materials interesting. Best lecturer I have ever had. As long as you do the work, the grading is not bad at all. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('773', 'Lots of readings, 3 3-4 page response papers and a research paper. Miller tends to follow the lecture style but if you enjoy History you will find him interesting to listen to. Course material is interesting. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('774', 'This was an okay class; the professor is intelligent, but she is very kind and often lets less educational class discussions go on because she doesn''t tell people their ideas are not well-formed, so can be a frustrating class period efficiency wise. The final research paper will be a fair amount of work, and she will grade relatively severely, but definitely rewards decent writing. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('775', 'A lot of work, harsh grader ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('775', 'Very fun course; decent workload ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('776', 'Very interesting topic. Professor is knowledgeable and engaging in lecture. Moderate amount of workload. Worth taking if interested in High and late Medieval history ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('777', 'It''s not too difficult, but the class has a lot of work: paper, midterm, final project, reading for every class. The lectures are pretty disorganized. The professor asks many questions about the readings throughout the class, and most people in the class seem to be white frat boys and sorority girls. So the class discussion quality is pretty low with very few insights. The readings are interesting and the class topic is fascinating, but the way the prof interacts with the class is boring and not very insightful. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('778', 'Great course, workload was relatively low, grading was fair, nice professor, very clear expectations, materials were very engaging, although lectures were sometimes a little boirng ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('779', 'Lecture-heavy class. 4 papers in total. Prof is really great if you love history, but can be dry if you don''t enjoy the material. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('780', 'Great prof! Engaging and funny. Material is interesting but you might not learn a lot if you already know a lot about 20th century Europe. Workload is reasonable. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('781', 'Illuminating class on revolutionary history. Took it because of Hamilton but got engaged in the grander scheme pretty soon. Workload manageable. Discussions could get a little repetitive depending on fellow classmates. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('782', 'Very hard class. Grading was harsh. 150 pages of reading and 1-2 hours of compulsory film watching every week. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('783', 'Good professor, very knowledgeable in modern and ancient Middle East, would recommend if u like to read ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('784', 'Typical history class. Expect heavy readings. Professor gave out clear instructions and exams were graded fairly. Mandatory class attendance though ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('785', 'This class can be taken as an MMS certificate elective. It''s a lot of reading and work but professor is always willing to help you out. Bear in mind that class participation is very important for this class. Make sure you don''t skip class and talk a lot. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('786', 'A really really good history class. Learned a lot about the history of South Africa under Apartheid. Recommend also to people who majors in PubPol. It counts as the history elective and you definitely get exposed to things you wouldn''t encounter in Pubpol. The readings sometimes are tough and hard to understand, but in general, the work load isn''t too bad and it''s worth the time. I''m not sure about the grading yet, but the professor is such a nice person. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('787', 'Really chill class, but I don''t think it''s offered every semester. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('788', 'This was required for DukeEngage: Beijing. If you want to know more, talk to me. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('789', 'Chill class, introduction to different religions but you don''t necessarily learn something deep besides the basic religion tenets, populations etc. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('790', 'this house course is about sex education. everyone in the class is very sex-positive, pressuring others to conform to the culture too. the course provides very useful info tho. everyone in the class is white except me, and the class discussion is almost entirely about fraternity and sorority life regarding sex. instructors are students not the prof. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('791', 'Chill pass/fail philosophy house course with 2 writing assignments (don''t need to be amazing). Readings are pretty much optional. Interesting house course to take if you want a half credit - you don''t need much background knowledge to engage in a cool discussion on these paradoxes. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('792', 'A lot of writing and wired challenges, good course to take if have free time ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('793', 'intersting case studies and knowledgable guest speakers every lecture, light assignments and workload, good network ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('794', 'Personally I think this class is pretty bull shit. Well it teaches you how to be an entrepreneur, but I don''t think anyone can teach anyone how to be an entrepreneur. There''s a good part tho--there''s a guest speaker everyweek and they usually are some Duke-related entrepreneurs who are fairly successful. I did learn quite a bit from them as their speeches were properly insightful and inspiring. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('795', 'Interesting content about entrepreneur especially in the field of medical devices. Light workload ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('796', 'Very practical class covering valuation, financial statement, price strategies, and other concepts relative to entrepreneurship. - 2 exams with assignment composed of readings, group projects, and case studies. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('797', 'Kathie is an amazing professor and this class is interesting and useful - a ''mini MBA'' of some sorts. You learn about financial statements, marketing, pitching, and work through many HBS cases. It''s also an easy A so I would recommend to anyone, even if you''re not considering I&E! ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('798', 'Lots of semi-mandatory reading, lecture heavy. Very ideologically and philosophically based. Workload is manageable - 3-4 small essays and one big research paper. Miller is a cool guy but you gotta be interested in the topic to find his lectures engaging. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('799', 'Materials interesting while ideological, workload relatively large, lectures are a bit boring but professor is very willing to improve upon feedbacks ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('800', 'A lot of work, interesting material, decent lecture ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('801', 'Course focuses on addressing global issues from the perspectives of victims (primarily non-Western countries). Expect a lot of reading and writing. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('802', 'The best course I''ve ever taken so far. Amazing lecturer who pushes you to think about the world on much more complex levels than you''re used to and challenges your assumptions. You''ll gain so much: solid writing skills, research, critical thinking. Content can be very biased (condemns globalized neoliberalism). ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('803', 'great prof. don''t bother if you know little about Middle East. Not a 101 intro class. Would be great if you want to know more about middle east politics, economy, religion and history ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('804', 'good professor to take this with! workload is heavy like ICS 195, but Meyerhoff is super nice and not a harsh grader, and the material is interesting ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('805', 'Awful class. I DO NOT recommend a class taught by this professor, EVER. The amount of work to getting a decent grade ratio is completely unfair. He is a PhD student at Duke, and I felt as if I was doing a majority of his research in this class. We did absolutely nothing related to what the course description said. He is a very dry lecturer and very unreasonable professor. For creative projects, he ends up expecting everyone to use the same fundamental tools and concepts (which is ridiculous). He is never clear about his expectations, and when he is, it''s 1) too late and 2) way too unreasonable (the number of pages or deadline). We were supposed to learn how to use different digital tools such as Photoshop, After Effects, Google Sketchup, etc. but we barely covered the basics for all and any of these tools. He prides himself on not giving perfect grades and will take off a ridiculous amount of points for something very miniscule. This was an awful class that I learned absolutely nothing in and wasted way too much time. I can honestly say that everyone in my seminar class *hated* it and wrote awful course reviews; some students even petitioned their grades. Do NOT take a class with this professor. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('806', 'Awesome! Professor is enthusiastic and prepared. Learn about unity a lot, workload average/chill ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('807', 'Harder than 101 probably I had a stricter professor. But she really allows you to learn what is the best way to learn languages in general. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('808', 'First level Japanese. Endo sensei is very experienced in teaching Japanese and very helpful. No curve for grading but you should expect a good grade if you do all the required work. Homework everyday. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('809', 'Four classes a week. Homework everyday. Quiz almost every class. Very easy and both instructors were really nice. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('809', 'All language classes at Duke are tedious. Japanese is easy for Chinese. Gotta work everyday for this class. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('810', 'Really fun class, professor is very nice, but strict with homework submission and class attendance and puctuality. Managable workload, easy A. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('810', 'Very fun class to have. Class attendance and participation are important. Easy content and easy A, but daily homework. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('811', 'The class meets four times a week and we have homework everyday. The teacher is cute and funny - I loved her class so much! A lot of work, but as long as you put in effort, you should be able to get a good grade. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('812', 'Not very difficult. Professor is really nice. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('813', 'Second part of first year Japanese. Slightly harder than JPN 101. Projects start to be fun since now you can express a lot more things in Japanese. No curve for grading and 1 hr of homework everyday. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('814', 'Four classes a week. Homework everyday. Quiz almost every class. Very easy and both instructors were really nice. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('815', 'The class is getting more difficult as it unfolds. A lot of work. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('816', 'Regular workload, interesting class projects to practice Japanese ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('817', 'Very interesting class. Daily homework and lots of quiz, projects, and assignments but pretty easy. Very strict attendance. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('818', 'Fun as always. More difficult than elementary level but manageable and still easy A ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('819', 'It''s a great leap from 203 - a lot more difficult stuff, super heave workload, very strict gradings, and very fast-paced lectures. I don''t enjoy Japanese anymore. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('820', 'Daily assignment and weekly quiz/essay. Easy A if you put efforts into the class and try hard. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('821', '*3 times the workload of Internmediate Japanese. But still easy A if you put efforts into the class. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('822', 'Pretty chill class but a lot of characters to memorize; also contains oral presentation ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('823', 'Kurokawa-sensei nice and cute as usual ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('824', 'Very fun and very discussion-based. Class is only twice a week so workload is heavy. You get to talk a lot in class. Lots of presentations. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('825', 'very fun, easy, great teacher, highly recommended ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('826', 'Best class ever at Duke I''ve taken so far, I''ve learnt so much about a language I knew basically nothing about before. Professor Kim is the sweetest little Korean professor you will ever meet, she is extremely nice and I always see her helping students who struggle, so she''s definitely accessible. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('827', 'The professor is super nice and teachers pretty well. The class is fast-paced. Expect a lot of work to do. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('828', 'Easy and fun course with a great professor! ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('829', 'If you search for prof kim on rate my professors, she''s rated a 5. Because she is just that awesome. Super friendly, helpful, cares about her students, clear - I would not have learnt as much as I did without her teaching. And it''s really easy to get good grades in this class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('830', 'Prof Kim is the nicest person you will ever meet in your entire life. I''m totally serious. She grades super nicely (pretty sure everyone in my class got above a B+), is very chill, teaches well, and really encourages a fun class dynamic. Probably my favourite class at Duke! ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('831', 'I will never have enough good things to say about Professor Kim. She is the nicest!!! This class, on the other hand, was definitely a step up from the previous class. You learn a lot more history and do a lot more reading + writing, so if you want to focus on those aspects of the Korean language, take this class! ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('833', 'Language class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('834', 'Professor can be a little daunting at first. She is extremely knowledgeable and has very high standards for her students. Big workload. But if you love Latin epics, this is a class you need to take. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('835', 'Pretty cool course taught by doctors from Duke hospital. Nearly no homework and half of the lectures are by guest speakers. Exams are really easy and staightforward. No reason not to get an A for this course ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('836', 'Discussion based course. You can scan the readings and still do well in discussions. We wrote a few blogs, had one essay assignment, one in-class exam and the final is a group essay. Professor Paredes is a nice person but a little bit unclear about the grading standards. Being active in discussion and talking with her about essays definetly help earn a high grade. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('837', 'Passionate professor, not lots of reading, on line open note exams, but sometimes not the most organized professor I have met. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('838', 'Extensive knowledge on discriptive linguistics. The textbook is fun to read and the prof from Britain is funny. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('839', 'very intro level course and I feel like I went back to my freshman year. Material inclusive. Professor nice. Cannot remember workload so I would say it is light. however duke linguistics is highly social linguistics etc. so if your interest is computational linguistics you would be probably disappointed. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('840', '3 midterms; no final; homwork counts towards 25% of the grade. No a hard class overall; Make sure you do the readings and memorize the textbook. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('841', 'The professor is great, and the class is interesting. But sometimes the lecture got really boring. We had guest speakers who speaks the language we learned that week. Two term papers to write and that''s it, though the grading scheme is not very clear, because she didn''t grade it - it was graded by the grader. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('842', 'A class in Neurosci & Law Focus Program. Do readings and take good notes in class. Participate actively in class. Exams and papers throughout the semester. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('843', 'Two papers, a blog with weekly post. In focus program. Really fun and chill, learned a lot of stuff. Good intro to linguistics. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('844', 'Best class ever taken. It''s part of the focus ''Power of language'', in which we examine how language influences politics and ideologies. Totally changes my whole life. And Professor Price is both knowledgeable and funny, with a British accent. :) ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('845', 'Edna is the most adorable professor I''ve ever met! And she''s so organized in class, while keeping the class as interesting as possible. Her exams are straightforward and all the questions are from the past homeworks. And she will give out review sheets with all the possible questions on the exam. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('846', 'Most interested class in college. Focus class but with a lot of information and insight. Tests are based on homework so everything is under control. (no surprises) ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('847', 'I would deinitely recommend this class to anyone interested in gender studies or linguistics. Professor was very knowledgble and class was fun and engaging. You have to do all the readings though since you will need to hand out a short report in every class. Plus, professor is a easy grader so you''ll be good as long as you do your work. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('848', 'Really interesting material if you like scifi, professor is nice and willing to offer help outside the class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('849', 'Lit 190s offers different topics each semester with courses carrying multiple codes. Intro to Transgender is a new topic in this series, which approaches the topic from a lot of angles including biology, philosophy, statistics, arts, etc. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('850', 'Tons of code (STS, EI, W, Seminar, etc...) Interesting topics (especially the porn unit - yes you actually watch porns in class and for HW), but Bobo is really kind of weird (aside from his name). Not as easy/fun as I hoped, but I did learn many things. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('851', 'core course for lit major, not a super easy intro course because the grading can be harsh and the take-home midterm is a lot. But you certainly learn a lot and Robyn is a good teacher ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('852', 'The course doesn''t require a lot of readings, but the reading materials are hard. Three critical summaries per semester. Professor is accessible and helpful. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('853', 'This course is the core for Lit majors and minors. A comprehensive overview of critical theories - colonialism, the politics of matter and agency, capitalism, and such. Professor Wiegman is wonderful. Three critical analysis (bascially 3-page-summaries of the readings) and a take-home midterm and final. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('854', 'Material is very interesting, but the prof could be more engaging. She touches upon only the surface of each story and her analyses lack depth. Overall an easy class, but not sure how much you could learn about literature. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('855', 'Really interesting material, although the professor didn''t really do a good job to make the discussion intellectually challenging. She could be a little vague about expectations for papers, but in general grading was lenient ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('856', 'Loved the course! Core course for lit majors. every week there are assigned movie(s) and readings, and we would discuss films and theories in course. Both professors are knowledgeable and caring. The course really engages your critical thinking ability and challenges you to question the things you''ve taken for granted. It is one of the courses that you will remember for a long time even after you graduate from Duke and feel so fortunate and proud that you''ve taken it ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('856', 'One of the most interesting seminars. Chow is very knowgeable about Asian culture, media and critical theory. The class itself is exploring critical theories (Freud, Lacant, Foucault etc) through Hitchcock''s films. Mainly discussions of the films we watched for the week. Two big essays (10-15 pages) and several reading quizzes. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('857', 'Professor Dorfman is no longer teaching, I guess. But this class is one of the best you could get as a lit major. Basically reading obscure yet fascinating Latin American/African novels and discussing them. Prof. Dorfman is the rock star of the department. He''s friend with all those authors and his own works are stunning. Just listening to the man talk is quite an experience ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('858', 'This course is half undergrad half law school students. Workload is reasonable and content is super interesting! 75% of the grade is the final, though, which can be stressful. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('858', 'Law school class that undergrads can attend. Engaging materials, experienced professor. Three response paper and an open-book final exam (counts for 75%of the grade). Recommend if you are pre-law ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('859', 'Graduate level lecture on world literature with a healthy dose of philosophy and world history. Just be there for Jameson''s sake. Pure Lecturing. Enormous amount of readings. But pleasurable. Grading is mysterious ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('860', 'Pretty cool and interesting intro to literature class at Duke. Meet two times a week, decent amount of reading. One reading note per week, and two 15 pages essay. No final. 装逼神课 ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('861', 'intro math, for those who didn''t take AP, the professor has a very detailed explanation on each topic. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('862', 'He is the best MATH professor I''ve had in my life! The class grading is a little bit frustrating and getting an A is hard, but you learn a lot in this class. I''m sure you will love this professor as well! ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('863', 'Easy material but kind of hard to get an A because the class was harshly curved. Professor was great at explaining things and always helpful. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('864', 'The professor is nice. He goes not too fast and doing homework would help a lot. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('865', 'Easy ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('866', 'Easiness: This class is quite challenging like all Duke Math. There are three midterms, many quizzes, labs, and more. Also, the grading is extremely ambiguous. Note: Yu Pan, however, tries her best to make it as clear as possible for her students. Definitely talk to her as much as possible and make use of her math help room hours. Workload: 5-6 hour per week ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('867', 'Nice professor but very difficult class. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('868', 'Skip if you can ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('869', 'Don''t take Calc II at Duke if you already have credit for AP Calc BC. Waste of time and may not boost up your GPA at all. It''s known as the ''most failed'' Math at Duke. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('870', 'An okay class. Shouldn''t be hard if you do study. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('871', 'Material is pretty easy if you have taken Calc before but the lab portion is a bit time consuming ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('872', 'Do the hwk, work really hard for that A. Sarah is a great prof and she is very helpful and she does great notes ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('872', 'Single variable calculus. Recommend taking. Really great professor. Has a lab section and requires some group work. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('873', 'Very hard. Not recommended. The most difficult math cpurse at Duke. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('874', 'She''s a grad student and taught really well. Do the homework and go to class, you should be fine. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('875', 'A little bit heavy workload and harsh grading ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('876', 'Very easy A seminar, because all the materials are based on high school mathematics. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('877', 'Do not take this class if you are only looking for a QS code, I repeat, DO NOT TAKE IT JUST FOR A QS CODE ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('878', 'Do the homework, 4 hours a week ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('879', 'Class is supposed to be easy; it has both linear algebra and calculus stuff; make sure you know the lecture slides; quite easy in general if you go through the material every week ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('880', 'Easy. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('880', 'Don''t skip class and do the work. You''ll be fine ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('881', 'The professor is, I heard, the best for this course. She''s really passionate about math, to the extant that she would go off her topic while teaching this class... I really like her, though some people finds her unclear and spends too much time diverging the topic. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('882', 'Easiness: Duke math is never easy, and this is no exception, though I have heard that this class is easier than regular multivariable (MATH 212). Workload: Not that much work at all. There is one problem set per week, which are normally not too hard, except sometimes can be rather tedious. These problem sets are graded based on accuracy, so it is important to do them neatly and precisely. Comments: The class satisfies both my math requirements for my Econ and CompSci majors, which is a major bonus. The tests are difficult, and Professor Hahn moves through the course material very quickly, which can make the class challenging. I would recommend going to her office hours, because she is a lot more helpful one-on-one. Her lectures can be very dull, but she is a very funny woman which makes class fun sometimes. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('882', 'The class material is very easy, however, it doesn’t match whats on the exam. It is more of a linear class than calculus. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('882', 'Very helpful for Econ205. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('883', 'Midterms are easy, but professor is not good at teaching. Get ready to self learn ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('884', 'Take Roy''s class if he is teaching this course!! Go to his class especially the last week and you will use his one system of method to solve everything lol. Favorite prof. Very smart and good at teaching. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('884', 'he''s a very good lecturer. Workload manageable. Never collects homework.A few take home quizzes ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('884', 'It is quite a challenging class, but as long as you keep up with the class you will be fine. Professor Roy is extremely helpful. Please take his class whenever you can. He teachs both math and physics. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('885', 'Very funny professor and friendly to all of his students. He''s good at explaining concepts, but not necessarily in giving feedbacks on HW. Good resource to gain insights and inspiration for math study. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('886', 'Good professor, ok work load ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('886', 'Weekly problem set ungraded, could be used for extra credit later in the semester. He gave out inclass quiz first half of the semester, then take home quizzes which are harder second half. 2 midterms are harder than some other teachers but that give you an edge with the block policy ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('887', 'HARD COURSE. GOOD PROFESSOR ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('887', 'Concept is difficult for me but I heard it''s easy for a lot of other students. Brian teaches very well and is very willing to help. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('887', 'Let''s be honest -- it''s a hard course, and anyone who told you the opposite is either a Math genius or someone who worked his/her ass off but pretending to be a Math genius. However, Brian is a awesome professor who''s super passionate about the subject and makes the course less miserable. Study hard and you''ll get a good grade. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('887', 'Excellent professor but quite heavy workload. The material is a bit hard ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('887', 'Great professor. Reasonable workload and his midterms are easier than other professors'' ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('888', 'Not hard in terms of the exam as long as you finish all the past exams. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('888', 'His exams are straightforward, but the material is not very easy. ' );
