INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1075', 'Class is knowledge based over the stories and style of the composers. Also analysize specific pieces in class. Need to write two papers over specific pieces/composers that could be challenging without robust background in music theory. Also has listening quizs so need to know the pieces well. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1076', 'Great professor; fun class; lots of learning; need background in music theory ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1077', 'Mandatory for music majors. 4 classes per week, including 2 labs with singing, dictation and keyboard. Heavy workload ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1078', 'Homework is not hard but annoying, a lot of details to be taken care of. No midterm no final, but class participation is important ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1080', 'Great course to learn some basic conducting - you don''t necessarily need music 361 to take it ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1082', 'boring/difficult theory class; need to take theory 1-3 prior to this class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1083', 'Best theory class I''ve ever taken. Really easy to get an A. Just do the homework and participate in class. Doesn''t even require that much participation. Professor gives you a change to redo hw as many times as needed ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1084', 'Most interesting and challenging class I''ve taken because it was a grad seminar. But professor is really knowledgable and really nice. Allowed me to redo my final paper 3 times but maybe this was because I was an undergraduate ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1085', 'It''s interesting if you like classical music. The professor talks a lot and it''s very easy to fall asleep in class. He can work with you on grades. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1086', 'Lectures are boring. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1086', 'The class is very easy and there are sometimes readings, but the final grade you receive is based mostly on three main projects that you do: a final research paper, an hour-long group presentation, and a final listening test (which can be hard if you don’t really know music).Professor Davidson is an incredibly kind instructor who always encourages students to participate. If you’re not interested in music, his lectures can sometimes get dull, but his passion for the subject is apparent in the depth of his musical knowledge. Also, the class features some really amazing guest speakers towards the end of the semester (such as a private Ciompi Quartet performance and a private Duke Chapel organist lecture/performance). Overall, a wonderful class! ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1086', 'Interesting materials but boring lectures. One big presenaton, one big paper and one listening examination as main evaluations. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1087', 'Boring but easy class. Professor is boring but nice. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1088', 'The professor is really strict and you need to memorize all the information by heart and be able to use them in different situations and case studies. There''s no shortcut in her class and it requires a lot of effort. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1088', 'An overview of neuro. Not much memorization but do need to memorize certain facts. Williams''s teaching style is energizing ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1089', 'Very knowledge based and introductory class. The midterms are not hard at all if you read the web notes, but the writing assignments can be annoying ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1090', 'Close book exams can be hard. Large workload because of memorization. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1091', 'Loved this class. Murphy is funny and knows her stuff, takes time to answer questions, explain things, and looks up questions she doesn''t know straight up know the answer to. Class isn''t too much work, plus tests are online, open everything (they''re more application-based). I looked forward to lectures. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1092', 'Interesting course material and Dr.Murphy is very knowledgable. However the exams can be a bit challenging. You need to understand the material to do well ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1093', 'Not too difficult. Does not require too much extra study. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1094', 'one chapter per week; lectures just repeat the textbook; weekly quiz questions are tricky and grade is tough; take neuroscience 101 ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1094', 'Minna is a very passionate professor and the class is interesting. However she could be unclear with her expectations sometimes. Tests are immensely hard with lots of details but project is not graded harshly. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1095', 'Flipped course, teacher is super sweet and nice. A lot of materials though ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1096', 'Team based class. You are responsible for reading and understanding the chapters on your own. She will provide a mini lecture on each chapter. It''s a flipped class and work in teams (solve application problems ) so people could whether like it very much or find it uncomfortable. I personally like this class very much. Dr. Ng is very nice. Not a very harsh grader. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1096', 'quizzes once per week based on own learning, which is quite a lot of reading; lectures barely cover the whole chapter and so again, self-learning; activities are fun and do help with memory somewhat; exams are based on textbook ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1097', 'Fantastic class, extremely easy. Prof Andrews is awesome and wants to make the class as easy as possible. Pretty impossible to get less than an A. Readings get redundant/become kind of unnecessary towards the end. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1098', 'Reasonable workload with readings and questions graded for completion every class. All quizzes and exams are literally verbatum from hw, and it''s very hard not to get an A in this class. Zero neuro/bio background is necessary. Very engaging and well-taught. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1099', 'I''ve heard Bilbo is better than whoever teaches in the fall. Not a bad class overall, basically a more in-depth Neuro 101. Bilbo is very nice and willing to answer questions outside of class. She teaches to the lecture, so study your notes/ppt and you will be fine. Reading the book is usually a waste of time. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1100', 'The materials are dense but very helpful if you are majoring in Neuro. Grading is not bad as long as you put in the efforts. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1101', 'Readings are very interesting but there are too many of them lol. There will be 6 quizzes testing on your understanding of the readings and can be hard to score an A. Midterm and final papers are not too bad. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1102', 'Neurohumanities in Paris program. It''s fantastic! Everything is like a dream coming true and suddenly you''re wandering in the museums of Paris or walking down the street of hundreds of years of history with all the famous people once lived there...It''s just simply amazing. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1103', 'Really enthusiastic and humorous professor; DON''T TAKE THE CLASS IF YOU KNOW NOTHING ABOUT NEUROSCI and don''t take it if you don''t care about phil; hard class but interesting material ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1104', 'DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS. It sounds interesting but Huettel''s classes are a huge PAIN unless you know your neuro. I didn''t know how to write the paper and bombed the midterm so I ended up withdrawing. Talk to me if you''re not a neuro major and you''re considering taking this. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1105', 'Prof. Huttel was one of the smartest person I''ve met, which means his lectures were kind of intense…fascinating topics but hard work. Make sure you go in with moderate neuroscience (or at least biology) background. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1106', 'The first part of the class is pretty much like Neuro 201 but it then turned to focus on vision. The combination of neurscience and art is interesting and inspring. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1107', 'The course is hard at the beginning because of the electrophysiology involved, but gradually it is manageable. Prof Bhandawat cares about his class and is very helpful when you reach out to him. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1108', 'The class structure and expectations are clear once you understand what he is thinking. Accent could be a problem but you''ll get used to it. A great class in general. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1109', 'Team-based learning class. For the first class, you do a reading and take a quiz, then get a short lecture. For the second class, you read a scientific paper and discuss it via application questions. The topics covered are extremely interesting but it does get somewhat indepth and the material is confusing. Tests are very straightforward, though. This class isn''t taught very often, so take it if you like neuroscience and get the chance! ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1110', 'Chill prof and easy material, good for fulfilling major req, Team-based learning ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1111', 'Easy A. Basically you can drop all your bad grades and it''s team-based learning so there''s always your group to rely on. The course content is interesting too and he brought in postdocs to talk about their researches. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1112', 'Moderate Workload. Most of work is done in class. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1113', 'Independent study again, so I can''t comment very specifically on this unless you happen to work with Dr. Rubin (cognitive psych lab, does fMRI work that Neuro majors can swing in their favor if you don''t want to cut up mice). For reference, his research focuses on autobiographical memory, but any specific project depends on what grad student you end up working with. There''s a lot of stuff about trauma memory though, so that''s not for everyone. Dr. Rubin is an eccentric man that any Psych major has probably heard about, but he''s nice if you get your shit done and don''t do stupid things like falsify data. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1114', 'Moderate grading. Interesting course. Great prof. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1115', 'Not easy. approaches subjects in a very distinct way of thinking. prof extremely intelligent ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1116', 'More writing than expected. Nice professor. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1117', 'It''s a nice intro class to the field of philosophy. You will go through ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1118', 'One of the best class I''ve ever taken. She let us pick the topic, and really minimal workload. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1119', 'The seminar version of this class is taught by phd students. Heather is a very kind and understanding person, but I feel like the course is not very well-organized. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1120', 'The class was pretty chill but unfortunately it was also a little boring. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1121', 'Very good teacher. Highly recommended ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1122', 'Interesting concepts and could be useful in some ways. Makes me think in a different way. Professor is really nice and easy exams. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1123', 'I''ve always really liked logic, so this class was especially interesting and fun for me. A lot of people in the class definitely struggled though (especially with the proofs), so don''t assume this will be an easy class. I''ve been told first order logic is a lot like coding, so if you like comp sci this class might be a good way to see ''coding'' from a humanities perspective. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1124', 'very useful class if you are a compsci/ece major. Exams are easy. Easy grader. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1125', 'If you need 1 more credit and don''t care about the codes. TAKE THIS TOO EZ OMG ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1126', 'Pretty easy class; you basically discuss logic mechanisms and have a little bit of homework each day, learned a bit about logic and how it works ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1127', 'This course has some math, some philosophy and a little bit compsci. It''s a good choice if you want to have a fifth course to fulfill the ALP requirement, or just want to learn more about logic. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1128', 'should be a essay course but teacher do not know what he is talking about ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1129', 'Class first seemed easy, but requires a lot of work by the end of the term. Class difficulty depends on the instructor. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1130', 'Fun class but kind of stressful ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1131', 'Lok designed a very distinct way of teaching. Fun and spontaneous if you''re good at the material, and you get to decide your own pace. Work load mostly depends on how comfortable you originally were with logic. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1131', 'Audited it and did all the work. Prof. Chan has a special sense of humor (depends on whether you can get used to it), and he makes his own website to teaching (good style)! Course is not so hard (especially when you have experience with logic), but not recommend to people who dislike maths. Workload is small (0-1h/week out of class??). Class attendance required. Need self-discipline. WARNING: THINK BEFORE YOU TAKE AN 8:30 COURSE. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1131', 'Course itself is a''ight but according to others this is prolly the hardest logic course (other professors teach it in a kindergarten way). Lok''s a PhD and obviously a tech nerd who built all the course website by himself including the homework submission/scoring system. Quite a nice guy and the course content is something you gotta learn in order to become a cool kid. Oh and it''s CZ you if you need this code just take it. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1132', 'Easy and boring class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1132', 'Typical British man with weird sense of humor ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1133', 'Fun and easy class. No assignment. Only easy tests ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1133', 'This class varies depending on different professors. In my class, there was no attendance requried and there was weekly quiz (which is a good thing) ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1134', 'the professor is really chill but seems to assign harder homework than other sections. Easy class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1135', 'Easy class! Professor is so chill. Would recommend. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1136', 'Nice that there isn''t a final paper, just 5 short (1-3 pages) papers throughout the semester. LISTEN to his lectures (which are interesting, he''s a funny guy), he basically wants you to regurgitate what he says in class (also beware of the TA - he lets the TA grade 3 of the papers so know what the TA is looking for as well) ' );
