INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1137', 'Picky/difficult grader ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1138', 'harsh grading ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1139', 'On modern philosophy. Quite heavy writing load. The professor is ok - he is nice and funny. However, Rosenberg is offering the class now and he is crazily smart. Take is with Rosenberg if possible. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1140', 'Good course with gray professor ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1141', 'Best philo professor. Take it. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1141', 'A course on classical philosophy. Awesome professor, interesting course readings. Covers most relevant fields of philosophy (ethics, epistemology, natual philosophy, etc). A great course to take for potential philosophy majors. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1142', 'Best philosophy professor ever meet in duke. Interesting content with two essays and two exams. Essays are more important than exams ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1143', 'chill class，15pages essay ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1145', 'This depends on the professor but LOL. This prefossor is very soft-speaking and slow-speaking. I personally prefer more enthusiastic approach to learning. Discussions someimtes are off-topic for a long time. Classes are usually divided into half lecture by the professor and half discussion, so class participation is anticipated. Readings are quite long. Oh, and I believe there are two essays (if you take it with this professor), with each counting for 40% and 50% of your overall grade. Grading is not easy, so do treat the essays seriously. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1146', 'Easy class, extremely nice professor. Mandatory attendance. Two essays and a take-home midterm. Some interesting disucssions, but the large majority of the class (30ish people) is usually on Facebook or doing other work in class. Extremely nice professor who is willing to read and comment on essays before you hand them in for a final grade. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1148', 'This course doesn’t require great amoun of work/time, should be one of the easiest class at duke''s philo department. Two mid term & one final, all questions will be given out before hand as review questions. Easy A. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1149', 'Cool course. Really chill philosophy elective as usual. Brandon is a great professor though his lectures can sometimes be too boring. He strives to be fair and isn''t too demanding. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1149', 'The content of the class is tremendously interesting and useful. The professor explain things really well but is kinda slow... ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1149', 'Pretty disorganised but interesting if you’re curious about the intersection of math, philosophy and linguistics ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1150', 'One of the most interesting classes I have ever taken! A mixture of philosophy, math and linguistics and a perfect SSH class for engineers! ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1150', 'My favorite class at Duke. Very interesting materials, involve both logic, philosophy, linguistics and math. Cross listed in linguistics department as well. A perfect SSH class for engineering students or math/physics/CS majors. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1152', 'Prof Wong is a kind, wise old man. He lectures very clearly (always aided by detailed powerpoints), and grades incredibly nicely. For this class, the work consisted of 2 5-6 page essays and a 5 page take-home midterm. If you are at all interested in Chinese philosophy, or want a chill but informative class, take this! ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1153', 'Very kind professor; class could be a bit boring if not interested in topic, but very insightful and easy course. Not a very harsh grader, reading encouraged but not necessary (in my opinion). 2 papers (6-8pgs) 1 take-home final. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1154', 'Took it for Trinity requirements. Extremely boring and useless. Grading is not necessarily lenient. Workload is fine. Attendance counts. Do not recommend. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1154', 'Very vague in class discussions but valuable suggestions on papers ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1154', 'Love professor Wong! Very nice and knowledgable. Maybe boring for people uninterested in philo (since the discussions are very spontaneous). Take it if interested in asian philo. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1154', 'Not much work to do, but the professor himself does not like his ideas challenged. Be ready to obey whatever he says and copy powerpoint phrases to write your papers. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1154', 'The most boring class I have ever taken. Took it for Trinity requirements. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1155', 'Interesting class. All about business. Two case studies and short response every week. Heavy readings. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1156', 'Very easy class if you participate in class discussion. Final project is a case study, but you''ll spend half a semester preparing for it. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1157', 'Incredibly interesting reading and enlightening professor. Still following up on existentialism literature to this day. Not sure what the papers are looking for though, and grading is strict for a philosophy elective filled with underclassmen. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1158', 'There is weekly one page response, but overall is reasonable. The class is really interesting. There are two papers but the last one is before Thanksgiving. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1159', 'Good class, but the professor is a very hard grader. Weekly reading response + 2 term papers. High expectation for writing. A LOT OF Readings. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1160', 'I strongly suggest everyone who has specific interests into certain field of philosophy (or really any subject) to do a independent research. This experience is amazing, and the fact that Prof. Wong is awesome in every single way only make it better. The way it works is you find a faculty member specializing in the field to be your director. In my case, I basically gave a research proposal and planning; we would have weekly discussions, and the grade is based on discussions, efforts and a final 30-page research paper (which is required for all independent research class in philosophy department). Take it if you have specific interest!! ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1161', 'Interesting class- mostly evolutionary theory. You''re challenged to always challenge your own understanding of nature and the nature of epistomelogy. Workload negligible. Grades solely depend on two exams which are relatively easy ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1162', 'very interesting ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1163', 'This class is easy A in my opinion. Just two tests and review sheet with all questions on the tests are given. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1163', 'A chill course with mediate workload, but it should give you some understanding of biology ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1163', 'Very minimal workload if you don''t do the reading... Pretty chill class, lecture-based and grades composed of two equally weighted exams (essay questions will be provided in advance). ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1164', 'Could be a bit dry for someone not interested in Aristotle; but easy ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1164', 'Great class. I really enjoyed the material and the lecutres. The workload is tough, particulary due to the dense nature of the philosophy reading. Term paper is long. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1164', 'Absolutely fantastic professor. 1 midterm exam+one long term paper. Grading is very lenient. Highly recommend for philosophy major. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1165', 'Rosenberg is an incredible philosopher and lecturer, just not in this class. An economics major would find some of his positions puzzling. Readings and midterm papers that are fairly graded. I would take any other class with him. But for Phil of Econ, take it with Hoover. Hoover is the only joint faculty in econ and philosophy so has a much more holistic understanding of the subject. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1166', 'Class is mostly based on lecture+discussion. Again, he is a harsh grader. And a lot graduate students are taking this class. Don’t take this class unless you are confident in your writing. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1167', 'This is basically a more in-depth version of PHIL263 Chinese Philosophy. A lot of comparisons made between Chinese philosophical theories and Western psychology, so that was pretty interesting. Again, Professor Wong is a very nice man (invited us to his house for dinner at the end of the course) and is not a tough grader. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1168', 'Prof Janiak is super funny and interesting (and knows a lot about this topic!). It''s 10% participation and 90% final paper - go to him for advice about the final paper, so you know what he''s looking for. Honestly, what you get in this class basically depends on the quality of your paper, so if you''re confident in writing a 5000 word final paper well, this is the class for you :) ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1169', 'Learn about professor''s book, Material Beings, which is a pretty massive argument in recent metaphysics history. One of the recent philosophers who will probably leave a name in history, Inwagen is a Notre Dame professor who comes to Duke only every Spring to teach this. Take it while you can. Difficult but not much work. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1170', 'Easy, super nice ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1170', 'Prof Neander is super nice and sweet (got us pizza for the last class, heh). I''m a little iffy about the way she grades, because after my draft she gave me a spew of compliments, but ended up giving me an A-… Ah well. If you''re interested in the mind, you will enjoy this class! 60% final 5000-word paper and the rest is participation, short weekly submissions and a presentation ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1171', 'This class is ok... the seminar is professor-talking heavy. workload is small. no writing or assignment throughout the semester, but one big research paper for final. Material is tough. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1172', 'Different things each class. Recommend. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1173', 'Good sport class, really improved my athletic performance ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1174', 'this PE class is much more intense than I first expected. It''s 8:30 every tuesday and thursday, so be prepared to get up super early to work out. Lisa is very energetic and encouraging! She''s flexible too. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1175', 'Lisa is the greatest instructor ever! She is really cheerful and kind. The class exercises build on. A getaway from work and stress. Highly recommend. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1176', 'Different sports exercise twice a week. You don''t get tired of the sports b/c you don''t do the same thing every time as other classes do. Take this class if you want to lose weight… ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1177', 'I love her! She''s very energetic and encouraging. Well-rounded course with cardio, weight-training, body weight, some yoga, etc. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1178', 'Nice twice-a- week work out sessions, the instructor was encouraging and patient. Sometimes gets very intense. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1179', 'Fun class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1180', 'Pros:1. You get 5 free runs down the course, excellent value. 2. Zero pressure, just show up and hit some balls and you pass. Cons: You can''t actually learn a lot, after all it''s not one-to-one ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1181', 'Very interesting class; a little intensive for beginners. Focuses on ''endurance'' so workload''s like 1 mile/class. Also teaches techniques and how to exercise ''smartly''. This class does a decent job to keep you away from freshman 15. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1182', 'A good coach. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1183', 'Useful self defense techniques for women. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1184', 'Don''t go to the class hoping you will be undefeable afterwards. NO. In real fight, all the techniques he taught won''t matter cuz you will panic and do stupid things. Cons: You have to wear a stupid black tights every class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1185', 'Really fun PE class. Learn how to throw people on the ground ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1186', 'Master Lee is the best! You get chance to go to tournament. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1186', 'Really cool. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1187', 'Master Lee is great in teaching Tae Kwon Do. And you can learn a lot of defensing, kicking techniques and tae kwon do forms. The class is really cool. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1188', 'Relaxing Chen Tai Chi practice. Tighter absence policy than other PE classes (3 misses max). ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1189', 'Definitely worth trying if you are comfortable with touching people and being touched. I learned to appreciate my body a whole lot more. Plus, a back up skill if nothing else work out for me in the end. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1190', 'LOL. Take it if you want. Yes you do have to massage others as well as be massaged regardless of your gender. And yes, towards the latter half of the class you do have to perform and receive full-body massage (because that''s how massage is like in real life LOL). It''s a fun class, but I think you can only miss two sessions in total so attendance is strict. It is once a week, and when I took it it was from around 3-5 something Friday afternoon. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1191', 'This course is really relaxing and chill… it’s hatha yoga and the coach basically teaches you how to breathe… not an intense yoga class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1192', 'An easy and applicable NS class. There are no weekly assignments, just some writing assignments and quizzes throughout the semester. Medium workload. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1194', 'pretty easy, very interesting, you actually learn useful things about working out ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1195', 'If you like sports and you are looking for a easy class, take this one. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1196', 'Really easy class; one final exam and a few tests of the reading and teaching materials; Welsh is an interesting person to know if you''re into basketball. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1197', 'Basketball player class. Medium work load with some writing and presentations. Easy A. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1198', 'I took astronomy as part of IB Physics back in high school, so there wasn''t much new material for me to learn and understand in this course. Professor Kruse is really sweet, and definitely knows his stuff. Don''t expect this to be a class about reading constellations, it''s actually physics! You will need to do maths! ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1199', 'He is a fantastic lecturer with a kiwi accent. He does stuff at CERN that he brings up in class which is pretty cool too. Easy class if you''re good at math or physics. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1200', 'The material is very attractive if you are into cosmology. The workload is not heavy, doing problem sets. If you master all lecture notes, you will be fine in exams. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1201', 'If you need an NS code and actually want to learn something about clean energy, take this course. The prof is renowned in his field. Grading is not harsh, but there is some workload: 5 problem sets, 1 midterm, 1 group project + paper, weekly reading & response. Small class with discussion. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1202', 'Physics in summer is much easier and the class is curved. Professor Roy is really amazing. He is a funny person and very good at explaining things. Experiments in the class were very interesting. Definitely not a easy science class. Workload is pretty heavy if you do not have much hard science before. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1203', 'Easy class, quiz and homework every week but it doesn''t take too long to go over the material, easy to get A+ or A ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1204', 'Not much to say, pretty easy ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1204', 'Mostly high school physics. Premed class, so be prepared to be surrounded by super driven people. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1205', 'Unless you are a huge fan of team-based learning or teaching yourself from the book, do NOT take Physics in TBL format! (Unless, of course, they''re only offering Physics this way now, in which case, tough luck :\) Gauthier isn''t the greatest professor - he mostly just reiterates the book. He also had a nasty habit of taking over from other instructors. This class was also full of miscommunication and the grading policy changed several times, but that might be because we were the TBL guinea pigs. Also, turn off Piazza notifications so you don''t have to constantly see people whining about not getting grades back 6 hours after the test. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1206', 'Although homework might be hard, I really like the professor and he''s really responsible and willing to teach. He holds a lot of office hours and gradings are fine. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1207', 'The homework assignments are really hard but I think they really help you learn the material. Ying is really organized and super on top of his stuff, so don''t expect a chill lecture like ever. His first midterm is really hard but his second midterm is much easier. Would highly recommend because you do learn a lot from him and you come out of it with a better understanding of physics. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1208', 'Already took Physics in high school so the class is pretty easy; quite a bit of homework though and the tests aren''t too easy ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1209', 'All high school stuff. Quiz every week but not time cosuming. Should be easy A. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1210', 'No mandatory homework, and discussion is mandatory, but the professor''s lecture is wonderful ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1210', 'great ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1211', 'Fun prof. Hard content compare to 151. Easier if you took AP physic BC before. Hard tests. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1211', 'Workload 3-6h/w. Take if you are confident in physics; Roy is a good lecturer but you will have to learn something by yourself. DO STUDY lol ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1212', 'During the lecture it is like high school physics; if you are fulfilling requirement, going to discussion is enough ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1213', 'Very engaging class! Light workload, explores all areas of physics. Good easy NS. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1214', 'Covers important topics in modern physics including quantum mechanics and relativity. It is accompanied by a lab session, which is not hard but thought-provoking ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1215', 'Professor Greenside is extremely inspiring and thought provoking. He is the reason I switched to physics major. Heavy workload because the class has labs, which are not related with the lectures (lectures are on modern physics while labs are mainly on optics). Prof Greenside has notoriously hard tests. I only pulled off an OK grade by doing lots of his challenge questions in homeworks for extra marks. A strongly recommended class if you like to be challenged. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1216', 'Interesting course on introductory quantum mechanics. This is more of a introduction to the ideas than the full theory. This course also has some introductory special relativity. The lab is also another big part of the class. Lots of optical experiments. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1217', 'Small work load, fair grade, good lecture, 830am tho ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1218', 'Prof Howell is one of the easier professors. Be prepared to spend some time on the Mathematica labs. Take this class for your trinity requirement if you want a different experience. The Hamiltonian mechanics offers a much more interesting and insightful understanding about classical mechanics than Newtonian mechanics. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1219', 'Tests are tough. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1219', 'Class is very heavily math-based. DO NOT take the class until you have taken differential equations. Professor Brown is decent at teaching and is a nice guy. Workload is not much, but is very hard. You are not prepared for the tests unless you fully understand all the formulae. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1220', 'If you want to get everything out of your EM experience, take it with Prof Finkelstein. Don''t do this to yourself if you are just want an easy A ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1221', 'Professor is boring and talk very softly. The physics itself is fascinating. The class started off quite simple but would be hard later on. Strong math abilities are recommended. Most people taking this class are physics majors. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1221', 'Interesting content and hard. Professor is not engaging during class. The class is heavily curved so don''t worry too much about exam grades (not many people can pass the exams). ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1222', 'A hard-core course with two intensive physics experiments. Two 20-pages long lab reports are expected. A physics major requirement course. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1223', 'Arya Roy is a great physicist and really good at using mathematics to describe the world. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1224', 'Lots of reading and homework. Textbook is Cohen Tannoudji Volume 1. Very valuable experience if you are a physics major. Be prepared to spend A LOT OF time on this. A rather challenging NS code class if you want just to get by your Duke life, but that''s fine. Chances are you are a Physics major if you are reading this. If you are not, give yourself a pat at the back. You deserve a Summa Cum Laude for whatever other major you are in. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1225', 'Professor is very keen and passionate in his course. You get the chance to go to CERN if you do research with him. I take it as a huge boost if you are considering graduate schools. I learnt a lot from him. However, he can be too busy to tend to you sometimes. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1226', 'His current focus is on granular studies and thin film flows. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1227', 'good reading material but fair lecture ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1228', 'The content is useful but I personally don''t like this area. The professor is engaging. Grading is lenient. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1228', 'Interesting content. Most people taking the class are graduates but the class is not as hard. Professor is funny. Grading comprises a project. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1229', 'Python-based inquiry into important topics computational physics including Runge-Kutta method and percolation. Medium Workload and some teamwork is expected. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1230', 'Easy seminar. Two one-page paper. Guranteed A ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1230', 'If you are looking for a easy freshmen seminar or NS, take this class. The class is also interesting. We visited the top of the chapel, some sound chamber, and the organ in the chapel. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1231', 'Awesome prof and awesome class! Definitely learned a lot. Adequate workload - some reading, midterm, and final project. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1232', '2 exams + 1 paper. Not an easy A class but you do learn a lot about how political institutions work in western systems. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1233', 'the prof is hilarious and enthusiastic. Little workload. Recommend for non-econ majors ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1233', 'Very easy class. Professor Munger is fun and engaging. Writing assignments are greaded generously and the questions for final exam are given in advance. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1234', 'Workload is close to nothing. Lots of readings assigned but you don''t really have to read any of them. Fairly easy class. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1235', 'Weekly reading is not mandatory, three response paper, easy A if you are interested in the subject, final is multiple choice plus short answer ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1236', 'Interesting class with reasonable workload. Professor is helpful, nice and chill. You will have to take two midterms, one final and write three reaction papers. Class average was around A- so as long as you make some effort, you should be fine. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1237', 'Great professor and great lecture. But he tries to make sure only a few people get A, and the grading is very hard. But I learned a ton. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1238', 'DON''T TAKE THIS CLASS ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1239', 'Cool and knowledgeable professor, but lots of readings; grading is fair, class average B ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1240', 'lots of readings ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1241', 'Moderate workload, a nice beginning to learn and analyze works of the most important political philosophers in history ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1242', 'You will love Scott if you love doing political tricks or game theory; professor loves math/cs majors, and you got lots of interactions; not a harsh grade, average B+ ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1243', 'Class is pretty interesting, reading-based and easy. Recommended for people who are interested in law ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1244', 'He is the god! He will kill some, and choke the rest. Take the course after this great professor and get ready to be savaged with tons of knowledge being paid back ' );
