INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1502', 'Awesome prof, but workload is excessively heavy. Depends heavily on your team. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1503', 'Required for stats major. Group-based. Not really well structured. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1504', 'Don''t waste your tuition. The class is like a blabber of nothing. You don''t learn anything and he doesn''t teach. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1505', 'The class brings a lot of hard modeling concepts but you don''t have to understand them all. For any assignment, you can just go to the professor''s office hours and he will tell you everything. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1506', 'Applied class. Great for interviews and projects. highly recommend. Don''t go to lectures, watch recording for 1.5x speed. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1507', 'Strongly recommend if you want to truly understand the core of statistical inference beyond stats BS requirements. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1508', 'Very acceptable workload, but would not be the best choice for the first class in ML ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1509', '2 people can follow his thoughts in a 50 people lecture hall. HWs are easier. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1510', 'Very nice professor. Super useful class to do all computation in python + review a lot of the computation concepts learned in other class ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1511', 'Rogers is more theory-focused than the other professors. You learn a lot about the history of theater but it could be boring ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1512', 'Awesome prof. Learned a ton. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1513', 'The instructor was a Duke graduate and she is not only gorgeous but also very good at teaching! She really cares about every one and talks to you after class. The only thing is that this class might not be as easy as other acting class. You get to write a lot of play analysis and reflections and do rehearsals outside class. If you do want to invest time in acting, do it! ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1514', 'The more academic, ''serious actor'' acting class. Jeff is extremely knowledgeable and good at what he does (directing), but he expects you to read, discuss, participate, and really engage in the class. And all you do is Chekhov. If you want to acting purely for a funsies blow-off class, take it with Jay O''Berski or Kristen Marks. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1515', 'Dana Marks''s class is simply inspiring and enjoyable. Her class is interactive -- instead of lecturing for 70 minutes, she begins her class with warm-up activities, short skit, discussion on the play (the only reading you have to do). Then she will go over theoretical stuff on acting, and then usually we will be performing parts of the play. Two papers in total, and one off-campus play-watching at Durham''s one of the best Man Bites Dog theater. Definitely a must experience ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1516', 'intense reading and weekly paper. Also a listening test, a singing test (if you can''t sing then you have to do a reading summary) and quizes ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1517', 'Pretty intense English/Theater class, majority of class was English majors. Sarah Beckwith is extremely knowledgeable and passionate about Shakespeare, but this class asks a lot of everyone. Grading is participation (10%) and two 9-12 page papers. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1518', 'I really enjoyed this class, especially great if you''re into issues related to Asian Americans and their representation/media portrayal. There''s a lot of reading, but it''s mostly plays, so they go by very fast (plus, they''re actually pretty good plays). Other homework is journal entries where you write about whatever and discussion posts. The final performance takes up a lot of time but is pretty rewarding. Claire is extremely knowledgeable, but sometimes overwhelms people with the speed she functions at. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1519', 'Very participatory course, we were on our feet pretty much every class. Relatively easy, with short readings and memorizing/performing brief passages. Good if you need a different/fun ALP. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1520', 'Class- easy and fun. Prof- Malone is knowledge and fun ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1521', 'You meet once a week and read out loud your script. Not a hard class as long as you show up to class and do your work ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1522', 'Self-explanatory class, basically a semester-long workshop on how to audition for theater grad school/professional theater. Expected to have something to work on every class (new monologues). Jeff is extremely knowledgeable about auditioning and gives good feedback. This class isn''t offered often and is really only relevant to people interested in doing a lot of theater work, but if you ever have any other classes with Jeff: do your work, be on time, be gracious. He''s fantastic if you stay on his good side, but if you laze around and don''t rehearse the work you present, he will get on your case for that. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1523', 'Class- almost no work at all. Easy A. Prof- Chill and nice ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1524', 'Really fun, easy class! There are a couple short movie response papers, 2 essays, and a final paper/project, but other than that the workload is extremely light. Mostly a discussion-based class, you will have to participate, but we also watched a lot of movies. Beth is extremely sweet. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1525', 'The instructor is from UVA and the TA is from Duke. The class will be conducted via conference calls in Perkins with students and the instructor from UVA . Quiz & homework every week; 2 exams (written + oral); taught in Lhasa dialect (which is not spoken in Qinghai or Sichuan Tibetan regions) ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1526', 'Great teacher very inspiring ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1527', 'One of the best classes I''ve taken at Duke. Love Professor Hong! He really knows his stuff and tries his best to maximize what students can learn in his class. Expect some writings for the class. Do your work and definitely an easy A class. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1528', 'Prof- Boring Class-Don''t really talk about new media (which I am interested in) and put a huge emphasis on the history and evolution of media forms. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1529', 'Informative; lectures can get a little boring. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1530', 'Professor is nice and helpful. Learned basics of Adobe After Effects and how to make 2D animation. Projects can be time-consuming if shooting for high quality. Would recommend. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1531', 'Really interesting class and fun professors, provocative discussions, but heavy workload, not-so-easy grading, lots of reading and writing ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1532', 'Covered basics of using Maya to create 3d models and animation. Projects can be time consuming especially towards the end of the semester. Learned how to create 3D models, renderings and basic character animation. Would recommend. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1533', 'Senior class for visual arts majors where you develop a project of your own ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1534', 'This class you develop your own arts project ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1535', 'Graduate level visual arts class that focuses on exploring still and moving image ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1536', 'Very interesting materials that teach you a lot about basics of Renaissance architecture. Professor Lanzoni is also very nice. Went on to be a research assistant for her on the related subject. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1536', 'Probably one of the best class experiences I had at Duke so far. Use 3D software to model Venice church. Helpful professor ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1537', 'Easy and interesting course material. Do the readings and show up to class, you''ll be fine. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1538', 'interesting course, great professor. VERY DISCUSSION BASED, quite a lot of reading, and a few essays. He''s a lenient grader though ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1539', 'this class is so disorganized and almost meaningless. the prof is very western-centric, as if the third world women are all suffering. the prof is very very biased and arbitrary. you have to go with her position otherwise you won''t pass this class. the grade of the paper (which is the only assignment of the class) entirely depends on if the prof likes you. so if you want to take this class, you need to go to the office hours. but clearly, the prof only likes the white girls in her class, not the black athletes, nor the ''international students'' as she called it. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1540', 'Great professor: does a very good job at leading discussions, available to meet to talk about anything outside of class time, super helpful; class has a lot of reading and participation is super important, but totally manageable and you get a lot out of discussions if you are engaged and ask good questions. There were a couple papers, but grading is lenient ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1541', 'prof rojas is very insightful scholar with field concentration in china. but his class is disorganized. every week we have long and dense readings, and the papers are very difficult to get a good grade. he''s kind of impersonal. it''s difficult to know what kind of person he is. the class is def NOT an easy class. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1542', 'Easiness: This class is extremely easy. There are three papers and that’s basically it. However, note that the class is extremely bland and boring. Also, way too early for mankind, but if you’re an early bird go for it. Or a feminist. Workload: >1 hour per week ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1543', 'Not too hard. Loved the professor ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1544', 'Even though the course material is not something that I am particularly interested in, the professor is extremely knowledgeable about the subject and has shown us a wide range of films, books, and photographs to learn about African culture. The coursework is manageable, and the homework usually just consists of reading a variety of texts and annotating them. The information we are learning is extremely different and unique to anything I’ve been exposed to before, and the quality of instruction is good. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1545', 'Moderate amount of work comparing to other writing classes. the professor is very talented. Found it very enjoyable. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1545', 'Read 2 books and some poetry; watched and analyzed 2 movies; Prof is a great writer and not a harsh grader; in-class discussion required; 1 paper, several reflective essays and 1 final project ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1546', 'Professor is nice and kind. Reading is not so hard, and may take 1-5h each week (depends on person); will make you an ''expert'' in some aspects of primates after these readings :) I don''t like biology but this is fun. 2 * single-person (2-3 double space + 5-7 double space) essay & 1 * group-of-2 research proposal (7-11 double space? can''t remember) and presentation, each not super hard work. Go to lemur center and that''s nice for people who are interested in primates. In general, if you work hard and schedule office hours when you are not feeling good, you will probably get an A. Learn APA reference style. I would suggest choosing it if you''re in second window. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1546', 'Pretty chill class, not much work, grading was clear ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1547', 'Discusses how western depict of Africa is stereotyped and inaccurate. Final project was to create a short documentary. Keep bugging the prof with your drafts you will be good ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1548', 'Really nice professor, and the course provides a different perspective of Africa. Grading is fairly easy, as long as you show the effort. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1549', 'Easy class with low workload. No longer offered b/c the professor is gone ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1550', 'Choose this class if you are interested in environment-related ethical issues. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1551', 'Avoid if you can. Content is super boring; professor doesn''t teach the readings or actual writing skills. Little to no feedback on papers. Learned absolutely nothing. However, course is easy and you will end up with a good grade. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1552', 'Readings not really necessary ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1553', 'Not heavy reading. Nice prof. Definitely not a hard writing class. Watch a lot of Disney movies :) ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1554', 'My ABSOLUTE FAVORITE class at Duke. Watched Disney films for homework and got to reflect on my own experience with Disney in my final paper. Decent workload but I enjoyed doing every single one of the assignments. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1555', 'Interesting topic, caring professor, but pretty heavy workload. Blog posts and class attendance/participation are absolutely mandatory. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1556', 'Easiness: This class is much more difficult than your other Writing101 classes. There are a lot of daily essays and “blogging”-styled writings in addition to projects and papers. Moreover, he generally only gives two A’s and the rest are either A-''s or B’s, which really isn’t that generous compared to other easier Writing 101’s. However, he is an amazing person and this is my favorite class. The topic was also extremely interesting. Note: he’s extremely liberal. Workload: 2-3 hours per week ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1557', 'Go to class. Attendance counts. A fair amount of reading. Just try to skim the readings and have at least one or two interesting points to bring up during discussions. He''s a pretty fair/easy grader, and he''s more than wiling to give you comments on papers before they''re due. Make the changes and you''ll get a good grade. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1558', 'Good and useful course ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1558', 'Workload is normal. Highly recommended if u r interested in capitalism, socialism and feminism. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1559', 'Boring class. Easy A. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1560', 'One of the hardest writing section to get in. Interesting topics. 2 in calss quizzes, one short response paper, lead discussion, and a final paper (include oral presentation) ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1561', 'Boring class, but easy to get A-. No hope for A ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1562', 'Philosophical writing class. Professor is pretty chill. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1563', 'If you are looking for a easy A writing 101, take this one. The professor is really nice, but the topic is boring to me. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1564', 'Easy workload, only five papers, great professor ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1565', 'interesting topics, but the professor doesn''t seem to know how to lead discussions very well :( he''s leaving after this semester though ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1566', 'Lots of works, the most intensive writing 101; grading is fair but kind of harsh; if you are looking forward to improving ur writing, good choice ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1567', 'Very loaded course. Possibly the most demanding writing 101. But worths it. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1568', 'Loved this course. The whole class was pretty close and the professor was awesome. Professor Eilbaum was an international student when he was in college as well so he knows your struggle and will do everything he can to help you out. You need to devote extra 2 hours besides the regular class time every week to tutor high school students in Durham. That''s some serious time commitment so keep that in mind when you bookbag this class. Other than that, it''s an excellent class and class average was around B+ or A-. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1569', 'Little reading. 3-7 page papers. Graduate student. Very knowledgeable and nice. Watched movies related to readings. Gave snacks and gift bags on holidays. 10/10 recommend. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1569', 'Decent workload, quite interesting material, easy A ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1570', 'Easy class. Taught by awkward but enthusiastic grad student. Class is like a standard lit class. Do readings if you''re writing a paper on the book (also, it helps for in-class discussions, unless you can BS well). Fairly lax about attendance: there is an attendance grade, but she gives 1 free ''mental health day.'' I ended up skipping all of i-week but still did fine. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1571', 'Choose it only if you are into the literary world. Things are hard to grasp if you are not… ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1572', 'Workload is okay, the movies are interesting, good backup for second windows ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1573', 'The workload was very heavy. I wrote 7 papers in one semester. The material was all about primates and experiments that are testing if they are cognitive ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1574', 'Professor is ok. Team work based. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1575', 'A midterm paper 20% and a final paper 60% which she works you through for the second half of the semester. Workload is very chill, you will be reading mostly neuroscience studies. Professor is super nice and funny, she also plans lots of engaging class activities. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1576', 'It''s a fun class in which we mainly write about the history of Duke and Durham. One big paper (10-12 pages), 3 short writing assignments and a final project (internship, oral history or a wikipedia entry). Davis is a wonderful instructor, though the materials can be dry sometimes. Grading is fair. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1577', 'So great, highly recommend. Learned a lot about capitalism, race and finance. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1578', 'Interesting material, lots of reading, 3 essays ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1579', 'Moderate workload, pretty chill class time with intellectual philosophical discussions and some other fun stuff; grading is fair; strongly recommended if you are interested in philosophy and/or psychology ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1580', 'culturally based, not so hard and the prof is easy. But the reading may be hard ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1581', 'Very nice professor, knowledgable and easygoing, but has really high standards on the essay work in class. Helpful in guiding you to the right direction during writing processes. Has a habit to make you write multiple drafts but his comments are consistent. If you try hard and genuinely make an effort, A is not a problem ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1582', 'Easy class. You are expected to partner with other people on final paper project. Many athletes. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1582', 'Light workload for writing 101. Nice and understanding professor. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1582', 'Probably easiest writing class > < The professor is so chill that she doesn’t really cares about deadlines and there are only two general writing assignments for the whole semester. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1583', 'Easy Class. Two essays for the class. Reading was intensive in the beginning but workload turned straight down after the first essay. Second essay was group work and was given a month to finish. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1584', 'This topic is really interesting, and professor Fullencamp was super cool (he''s a DJ!). We had a trip to Nasher museum and went through many interesting materials. Yet, he''s hard on grades. Speak up in class and you''ll be fine. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1585', 'Interesting readings. The prof is more free-style in terms of teaching, but he is cool since he actually writes. The feedbacks are not very in time ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1586', 'Fantastic class and brilliant professor; not too much workload and the topic is very interesting; besides the three novels, there is almost no additional readings for the semester; grading is okay and as long as you make efforts you could get good grades ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1587', 'Highly recommend. Amanda is very nice and knowledgeable. Minimal workload. Getting a good grade is not hard as long as you do the work ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1588', 'The professor is really nice and caring. Lots of readings, but grading is fine. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1589', 'Worst class I''ve ever taken at Duke. Professor is extremely boring and there is a lot of work each week. The class sounds fun but is not actually. Not recommended unless you wanna torture yourself and read tons of paper on Behavioral Economics without understanding what''s going on really. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1590', 'Awesome class! Don''t be afraid about the Rate my professor'' tough grader tag. She is really nice ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1591', 'If you can take writing with Joos, do take it ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1592', 'Professor Kaufman is really nice and easy grader. The materials were fine. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1593', 'Two papers for the semester ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1594', 'Haven’t completed this course this semester yet but up to now, the material has been relatively easy. The class itself is also a very interesting and I perceive the topics in class to be very relatable. ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1595', 'Docter Smith is the most responsible professor I have ever met. She is willing to answer questions and help revise your papers at any time. Grading is harsh compared to other writing classes but is very fair. You''ll learn a lot with her! ' );
INSERT INTO Comment VALUEs('1596', 'Regular workload. As long as you put in the efforts, grading is fairly lenient and group discussion can be helpful depends on your peers. ' );
